	(25, 4, 'Y', 'Csr & Social Service', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vayjayanti Pugalia', '1975-12-08', '9830845945', 'vpugalia31@gmail.com', '11A,Palm Avenue ,Ashok Towers Flat 7 B', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/vayjayantipugalia/', 'www.facebook.com/vpugalia', '@vayjayantisahariapugalia', 'www.facebook.com/sonaliscubo', '@vayjayantisahariapugalia', 'Vayjayanti Pugalia Founder Sonalis Cubo is a multi award winning social entrepreneur,life skill architect,profound speaker,contemporary poet,and working extensively to influence the community for a positive mindset for change. Vayjayanti is also the Founder of “iCubo” a platform mentoring and exhibiting the skills and creativity for children,where ‘i” stands for ink, innovation and information. Vayjayanti is the President of West Bengal Lfe Skills Council for Women Indian Chamber Of Commerce And Industry and also a core committee member of the very prestigious Jyotirmai Club. She is the Co-Chairperson at Merchant Chamber and Industry Kolkata,/CSR And Rural Development Committee and also a core committee member of the MLF Wing of MCCI. She has been awarded as The Times Power Woman by The Times of India and Exceptional Woman Of Excellence at the Women Economic Forum along with many other accolades and citations to her credit including Dr. Sarvepelli Radhakrishnan award and Dr.Sarojini Naidu International award for her contribution towards holistic teaching and her contribution towards the society. Vayjayanti has won the First Position in We-Pitch Womannovator Kolkata platform in social service sector supported by the MSME Ministry Government Of India. Vayjayanti has been acknowledged THE POWER WOMAN AWARD by Bengal Chamber of Commerce & Industry for her “innovative approach to social issues”. Vayjayanti is recognized amongst 100 Inspirational Woman of the year 2021 for outstanding example n advancing opportunities for women in leadership by “GWIA”. Citated with The Kolkata Entrepreneurs Award,Vayjayanti has been communicating strong messages to the society through her endeavors like Colours Of Innocence,The Kidopreneur Summit,The Third Eye Summit ,Think Local Cook Global which have become a brand by itself. Her strong footprint against body shaming has reached quite a flame by the campaign “Main Apni Favourite Hoon” which talks about self- love and celebrating womanhood. Her drive towards impacting', 'Sonalis Cubo', 'Founder', '16', '2021-06-30', '17 Ballygunge Park Road 1 st Floor Pallavi Apartments', 'kolkata', 'west Bengal', '700019', '9831399798', 'sonaliscubo@gmail.com', NULL, 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/vayjayantipugalia/', 'My achievements are various projects that I have been able to iniate in my car3er.Each teaching me the importance of its discussion and awareness to have a more educated community and also a more included one. Project Mangoes @10 year 2015 and 2017 More than 10,000 Mangoes were collected each year, distributed by children to NGO and schools,in remote access areas.This project got young children involved as they could contribute through their pocket money which was a start to their thoughts towads GIVING BACK.\r\n Project Har Ghar Roshni 2016 During Diwali fire crackers food sweets were distributed to children by the funds collected by children of Sonalis Cubo benefitting more than 100 children.\r\n Project Roshni 2014 More than 75 children got together and made diyas for Diwali and sold them to raise funds for the deserved souls,Again a project to get youngsters involved and teaching them the art of bringing smiles.\r\n Project Yaarian 2015 Children treated children from NGO to MC Donald\'s bringing in inclusiveness of status and humanity. \r\nThe Kidopreneur Summit_Probably the firat pan India Sunnit on child entrepreneurship between the age of 10 and 17years.It included panel discussions pitching and seed funding for the winners.Participated as audience by 400 spectators from education houses parents and children. \r\nThe Third Eye Summit-A Pan India conference on highlighting the issues and entrepreneurial qualities of transgenders which was participated by many successful queer celebrities and common people celebrating queer community.Seed Funding through entrepreneurial pitching was the highlight.Audience demographic was in 100 who came together in support on the community. \r\nColours of Innocence Season 1,2 and 3 participated by More than 75 children each season painted and donated their paintings for charity.\r\nCurating Think Local Cook Global 2 seasons created opportunities for women to showcase talent and feel empowered through culinary art', 'The biggest challenge which i faced was to get business houses and people from the corporate world to take notice of my projects specially once my awareness projects started getting bigger starting from The Kidopreneur Summit.Not To prove to them that I had a vision to impact minds was very difficult as no one was feeling confident of me to endorse me.But i did not leave my grounds if they wanted me to bring a certain corporate house first to start the show i persisted on my journey by doing so.Geting Enst n Younfg to Techno India to Srei Finance i got all to get going on my first ever awareness conference to highlight the plight of education pressure on children which is letting entrepreneurship take a back seat.The outcome was fantastic and post which i never stopped dreaming my projects and making them into a reality \r\nThe third Eye Summit was yet another challenge where no one supported me to talk about the queer community in a big way.I self funded awareness project which i initiated and till today people talk about thte same.', 'I have involved young children into philanthrophy by initiating projects where they can participate fund and work hard fore there by embibing the art of giving in them at a very early age.As young as 4 years old.\r\nThrough project like the kidopreneur summit I have toughed on the subject of beyond studies and have been able to make many parents and children take notice of small potentials in their kids to start practicing along with their stidies.Selling slimes to designing mandalas and selling to toys and merchandise.\r\nThe community was very closed on the queer community not knowing about the difference between hijras and transgenders through my project The Third Eye I have been able to create a bridge between the so called normal and the.Ebquiries and opportunities coming to offer skill development jobs etc\r\nMy projects on women empowernment have enabelled many women to realise their potentials and start home businesses in return adding to revenue and growth for their families.', 'I am a torch bearer of issues which make the society strong and inclusive.To work more for the trans community and child entrepreneurship has always been my prime focus.\r\nIn the future I plan to create more awreness and opportunities for women who do not see their potentials and need platforms to find their motivation and support.', 'I initiate thought.I influence minds through my projects and thoughts.I become a bridge for ends to help each other.I believe through my dialogues i have been able to give philanthrophy a new meaning which to create awareness networks and opportunities.', '[{"download_link":"files/aGbusg6sVLDv1dFJxHi5IyjHJvRt1wPoAWLX6jfD.jpg","original_name":"RIM_4842.JPG"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/PVHd8rUvaMBFaqyfYL5N6KObNNiOkAr79PNweH7z.pdf","original_name":"Awards Vayjayanti Pugalia .pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/XBN9MmEsZt75MTbabN4dFLmDHJfYlJMkrQzIcgvA.pdf","original_name":"Mentions.pdf"}]', NULL, '2021-11-03 16:37:09', '2021-11-03 16:37:09', NULL, 0),
	(26, 3, 'N', 'Enterprise', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'CA.Sangeeta Agarwal', '1965-08-27', '9007790008', 'a.sanjay9@yahoo.com', 'Flat 2A,Parag,2nd floor,18/14 Dover Lane,Kolkata-700029', 'https://wmec.icai.org/article.html?article_no=846', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'I qualified as a CA in 1989, after a one year training with ITC Ltd and became a stock broker, partially influenced by my great grandfather, who was the first Indian president of the Calcutta Stock exchange.\r\n\r\n Taking up the membership of the NSE my stock broking company went public with its shares listed on Calcutta,Jaipur and Cochin stock exchanges, and I became the country\'s first professional woman to head a publicly listed stock broking company as its MD. Subsequently I took membership of the NCDEX .\r\n\r\n Despite facing repeated nerve shattering personal tragedies, and professional challenges, I guided my company astutely, delivering more than 100 % growth, year on year.\r\n\r\n My achievements have fetched me more than 40 coveted awards/recognitions, including the FICCI –FLO Outstanding Woman Professional award, from the then Finance Minister of India Mr.P. Chidambaram, The Indira Gandhi Priyadarshini Award, from the ex Defence Minister of India Mr. KC.Pant,The Rotary Club of Kolkata Award, The Outstanding Young Person of West Bengal Award, from the then Sports and Transport Minister of West Bengal Mr. Subhash Chakraborty and the Bharat Nirman Award.\r\n\r\n I have featured in leading magazines, newspapers, and on TV, including national news.\r\n\r\n In 2011, at the height of professional success, I decided to listen to my inner calling not to live a life of success, but that of significance and to be engaged with a charitable cause, and closed down my flourishing business. I was fortunate to be offered the platform of one of India’s, and the world\'s, most respected Spiritual Masters, Gurudev Sri Sri Ravi Shankar, and joined one of his organization’s; Sri Sri Ravi Shankar Vidya Mandir Trust-(SSRVM) unit in Kolkata (Sri Sri Academy, a reputed CISCE affiliated School, in the city of Kolkata), as its CFO, where I am presently engaged.', 'Sri Sri Academy(Kolkata)', 'Cheif Financial officer(CFO)', '32', '2021-06-30', '37A, Alipore Rd, Alipore, Kolkata, West Bengal 700027', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700027', '9831181077', 's.agarwal@ssa.org.in', 'https://ssa.org.in/', 'https://ssa.org.in/trustees-and-members-2/', 'The key learning\'s and achievements of my career are:\r\n\r\n1.	Real learning starts after and beyond the classroom as there is no better teacher than real life experience.\r\n\r\n2.	There is no profession or career which is barred for women. Women can do as well as men, if not better, in every field where men have ventured, including the so called “taboo” fields, which  by convention, tradition, compulsion or otherwise have been barred for women. \r\n\r\n3.	There is no short cut for success. Success achieved through short cuts is never satisfying, nor is it permanent. One has to work hard to be successful, keep learning while doing so, and keep adapting.\r\n\r\n4.	Honesty and integrity, together with resilience are the cornerstone of success. It is never one\'s circumstances, but always one\'s character that will determine how long and how far one will go in ones chosen career.\r\n            \r\n5.	Self-introspection, leading to self-awareness, and communication, are the key to building your team on your way to success.\r\n\r\n6.	Main achievements are: (a) First woman to head as MD a publicly listed stock broking company in India. (b) One of the very few woman, (if not the only one) commodity brokers in the early nineties,(c) started from zero and built the company brick by brick, to reach a turnover of nearly Rupees 4000 crores , delivering a more than 100% growth year on year. (d) Received over 40 coveted awards/ recognition\'s. \r\n\r\n7.	Last but not the least; every one of us has a social responsibility too. We should not forget this, and at the appropriate time, at least contemplate, and if possible do, ones bit for society. Greed, wants and desires have never had any limits. Self-introspect, be self-aware and you will be shown the right path at the right time.', 'Choosing an unusual career; stock and commodity broking, in the late eighties/early nineties, which were traditionally exclusive male bastions, was bound to be challenging.\r\n\r\n I was fully aware of an unwelcome entry, and a nebulous and arduous journey ahead, but I was confident that with patience, skills, honesty, integrity and dedication, I will achieve my goal.\r\n\r\n Initially, the biggest challenge that I faced was acceptability. People were not used to dealing with a woman stock broker and they thought that being a woman, I had ventured into this field as a non- serious player. Due to ignorance and ill information, being skeptical, about dealing with a woman stock broker, many potential clients, initially, even refused meeting me.\r\n\r\n I had a very rough journey initially, building my company virtually brick by brick, person to person, only by word of mouth publicity.\r\n\r\n Apart from professional challenges, I also faced repeated nerve shattering personal tragedies and traumas, including losing my son (only child) to a life threatening disease. \r\n\r\nAmong the four persons comprising my parents and in laws, three suffered from cancer. My father in law was run over by a bus and was on the verge of losing one leg. But these were small difficulties compared to what I had to face with my young son (at that time only child). He was diagnosed with a congenital life threatening condition, and despite my best efforts, I lost him.\r\n\r\n These personal challenges were far more heartbreaking that the professional ones faced by me .God chose me to undergo these personal challenges. I could not overcome them. Professional challenges were man created and therefore much easier to overcome. I knew I will be able to overcome them easily. With blessings from my mentor Gurudev Sri Sri Ravishankar,I have now accepted and reconciled to everything.', 'I was a pioneer; being one of the very few women stock and commodity brokers when I began my career.\r\n\r\nThrough, patience, hard work, integrity and honesty and above all the support of my family and the blessings of God and my spiritual Guru Sri Sri Ravishankar, I proved myself to be successful in a male dominated field. This broke the taboo that stock, share and commodity broking, which hitherto were “men only “occupations, could easily be breached by women.\r\n\r\n The very same men who were very unwelcoming to me during the initial stages of my career; thinking of me and treating me as an intruder, were the same people who subsequently applauded my work and decorated me richly with awards, honors and recognition. \r\n\r\nThis paved the way for many women in the society who may have been keen at that time to join this profession, but were unsure of doing so, to ultimately see, hear, read or come to know about me, and that encouraged them to traverse the path laid down by me.\r\n\r\nToday, I am delighted to see so many women making a successful career in this field.\r\n\r\n Among the thousands of my clients, I had hundreds of housewives too, who had no knowledge or exposure or treating stock, shares and commodities as an alternative investment avenue to generate wealth. I literally taught them from scratch, and was ultimately able to make them confident enough to use these instruments for wealth generation. This large pool of housewives in turn reached out to an ever larger pool of hesitant women, and like compound interest, this exponentially grew. So while we hear of initiatives like Millennium Moms now a days, (which is no doubt doing a good job), I had stated this initiative, albeit, silently a full decade earlier.', 'I quit as MD of my company in 2011, and left the profession of stock and commodity broking,as I wanted to listen to my inner calling and get associated with a charitable cause.\r\n\r\n By then my company was at its zenith, generating a turnover of nearly 4000 crores, thousands of clients, including some of the leading multinational companies, trading terminals, wide recognition, honors awards etc. \r\n\r\nBut this was never my actual intent. From the very beginning, I had entered the field of stock and commodity broking, not only with an intent or any strong desire for earning a monetary gain, but more so to take it up as a challenge to prove to myself and the world that women can be as successful as men in uncharted territories or professions which are generally not taken up by them.\r\n\r\n This was my motivation and my inspiration for keeping on going despite all the hardships that I faced. Having achieved almost everything that I possibly could,as a woman stock and commodity broker by 2011, I saw no further possibility of personal growth, so I quit,as I wanted to live a life not merely of success, but that of significance.\r\n\r\n From early child hood I had this burning desire to be associated with a charitable cause. I was fortunate to be offered a platform by Gurudev Shri Shri Ravishankar. Any further plans in future will only be in these fields. I set up the finance department of the school which I am looking after as the CFO, and have nurtured it as my child. Once my role over here is over, I will do whatever the organization under the overall supervision of Gurudev decide for me. I also plan to assist my husband who is very successfully mentoring for free, poor,but meritorious students.', 'I have nominated myself in the ‘Enterprise Category’ for want of another suitable category, and also because I have been so advised.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, I think that even though the common interpretation of the word enterprise means an organization; be it a commercial or business enterprise or a charitable one, the real meaning lies in the ‘enterprising spirit’ within us, which has been commonly been defined as \'eagerness to do something new and clever, despite any risks; or also the willingness and energy to do something new that takes a lot of effort.\'\r\n\r\nIf this \'enterprising spirit\' is what the jury is looking for, then I think I am a perfect fit.\r\n\r\nWhen discrimination, deprivation, disease and death cannot defeat or dissuade nor dampen or discourage  the spirit of a woman, and she dares to display determination and not get despondent or distraught, and stays steadfast in whatever field she has chosen, and goes on to achieve spectacular success in that,then that woman is truly an ”Aparajita”.\r\n\r\nI think my life so far has been a perfect example of displaying this spirit.\r\n\r\nWhen insurmountable personal and professional challenges combined with repeated personal tragedies and traumas cannot shake the spirit or prove to be a deterrent to the indomitable determination of a woman, then that woman is truly an “Aparajita”.\r\n\r\nI think I have displayed both character and courage not to get overshadowed by transient difficulties and to stay steadfast in the achievement of my goals.\r\n\r\nWhen a woman displays exemplary courage, confidence and determination to be a pioneer to traverse on uncharted paths, becoming a path breaker, and shows the light for others to follow, then that woman is truly an “Aparajita”.\r\n\r\nI have been fortunate to have been born as an “Aparajita’ and wish that I die as one.', '[{"download_link":"files/KMhZY5MejFX27Z6v9GoYytagEF4QBIMKVQaZewOe.jpg","original_name":"IMG-20210811-WA0015.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/JqQJlvMZ4iycl9cF1EHOt3Qjm0j0XD43UzsQxBR0.html","original_name":"Video of talk given by CA.Sangeeta Agarwal.html"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/YGBFiouMXLS1UAxWfnuyhO5j0H003OuuegHpjoAf.pdf","original_name":"List of Main Awards, recognition, credits, etc.pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/VddiSMvOxyIyrFYvB39bAQQKrZ0phTUSs1j8ImSe.pdf","original_name":"Photos -testimonials etc 6.92 mb.pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/kSC3x4E4WFNBusnFMzN0IP8oIrkASQbYeiz9S1fS.pdf","original_name":"other documents- success story published by  iICAI and draft of interview scheduled to be published by New Indian express newspaper shortly.pdf"}]', '2021-11-04 16:11:08', '2021-11-04 16:11:08', NULL, 0),
	(29, 2, 'Y', 'Health & Wellness', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vidhi Beri', '1984-06-18', '9748755946', 'vidhiberi@gmail.com', 'Eastern Metropolitan Bypass, Mirania Gardens, East Topsia, Dhapa, Kolkata, West Bengal- 700105. West Tower Duplex, Flat no: WTD218, 18th Floor.', 'https://www.vidhiberi.com/', 'https://www.facebook.com/vidhiberi.healthcoach/', 'https://www.instagram.com/vidhiberi.healthcoach/?utm_medium=copy_link', 'https://www.facebook.com/vidhiberi.healthcoach/', 'https://www.instagram.com/vidhiberi.healthcoach/?utm_medium=copy_link', 'It’s not who I am underneath, but what I do that defines me.  \r\n~The Batman.  \r\n\r\nAn avid Traveller, mountaineer, thrill seeker, academician, classical dancer (did my arangetram in bharatnatyam) classical singer (sangeet Visharad) vibrational sound healer, urban planner, mother of two gorgeous children, a health coach, a lactation educator, an argumentative Indian, confident, opinionated, comfortable in my own skin, fashionista in my own head, a businesswoman, and a healer.  \r\n\r\nI seek to change and I change to seek.  \r\n\r\nAs someone who wanted to always understand the deeper reasons for our existence and pursue the path to develop into the finest versions of ourselves, led me to academic pursuits that delve into the development of the self and increase myself awareness.  \r\n\r\nChild birth was one such pivotal and transformational experience in my life. At the time, it didn’t occur to me that it would become a full-time career and in the pursuit of learning, I would be able to share my journey and help over 3000 young mothers like myself in navigating the trials and tribulations that childbirth brings. It acted as a catalyst to deeply understand subjects that I did not have an educational background in such as maternity, nutrition and birthing choices.  \r\n\r\nAnd This platform will be my transit route to reach out to all the beautiful talented, confident women (and daresay men!) of my generation and those before and after me, that one can succeed, even when they fail.  \r\n\r\nAnd how learning never ends!', 'H.E.A.L. (Health, Energy, Awareness and Learning)', 'Vidhi has coached over 6,000 clients globally in the last decade on plant-based nutrition, stress-free disease-free living through holistic healing practices. She empowers the individual by engendering human relationship management with food, the self and family unit. Her USP is her power to transform belief systems and health through her chemical free organic approach. All her clients are parents to children from 0–50-year Olds and she often finds counseling and healing in the parenting journey for the Indian diaspora her forte.  Her work on women\'s wellness and maternity is notable in AMRI, Fortis and Bhagirathi Neotia hospitals in Kolkata. Her articles and press coverages have featured in notable publications such as the Child Magazine, The Telegraph (T2), Indulge Magazine and the Dainik Vishwamitra. In addition to her private sector work, Vidhi regularly works with Annganwadi health workers in the villages of Rajasthan and Madhya Pradesh on woman and child health practices. Furthermore, her social work incorporates workshops on Menstrual education, counseling and hygiene at the NGO Ektara, Kolkata. The Women\'s Economic Forum, The Heritage School Kolkata, and other notable Montessori\'s have invited her as a speaker on parent and child health. She is the author of Decoding Motherhood published in 2020 and currently working on an early parenting guilt free, stress-free book simultaneously with a child nutrition and recipe publication.    Her latest offering is her Neuroimmunological Healing Program, Ninja for Moms Module, Family Wellness Plan to tackle recent parenting, family and anxiety issues that are a byproduct of the pandemic. These modules incorporate counseling, sound healing tools, self-awareness practices, self-love tools including affirmations, gratitude, visualizations and meditations to empower moms like never before to face unforeseen challenges.', '11', '2021-06-30', 'Eastern Metropolitan Bypass, Mirania Gardens, East Topsia, Dhapa, Kolkata, West Bengal- 700105. West Tower Duplex, Flat no: WTD218, 18th Floor.', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700105', '9073618072', 'upasnanand3010@gmail.com', 'https://www.vidhiberi.com/', NULL, 'The Ugandan landscape of Mbarara was my first direct exposure to maternity health and its possible challenges in a developing nation. As a Msc student in UCL, London, I had not foreseen that my dissertation in the decentralization of maternal health systems will ignite a learning and eventually transform my career path into Maternity Wellness Coaching. We all come into this world through a mother figure and that is the most banal yet challenging reality of life wherein there is a lack of training and ability. I see my contribution in the space of health as two pronged in the last decade: Maternity Wellness and Health Transformation. One specialization leads to the other. In the last decade, I can confidently claim to be a pioneer in breastfeeding education, support and counseling in the entire West Bengal state. If there is a gynecologist committed to lactation support, then he or she knows of me and my contribution to this field through private and public sector trainings. Childbirth was devastating and truly enlightening at the same time. Certifications is Clinical Lactation, Breastfeeding Education, Counseling, Child Nutrition, Pediatric Oral Care, Craniosacral Healing, Sound Healing, Ayurvedic Health, Health Transformation Coaching are all the feathers in my cap as trainings and courses undergone in a decade post becoming a mother. The mothers I have coached have influenced my decision to further coach and transform the health of all adults and children towards the goals of hormonal balance, weight management and disease reversal. Their faith and trust in my knowledge, counseling abilities and ability to adapt and learn have led me to qualify in all the above fields of work as a uniquely well rounded health professional.', 'A health professional is by definition not a medical professional but the patient oftentimes doesn’t see the difference and wants you to be their doctor. As a health and maternity wellness coach, I have used food and counseling techniques to often cure many ailments. But, this has organically challenged many doctors, gynecologists and pediatric opinions. There is no holy grail when it comes to curing human ailments. A 20 something health professional is too young to have any deep rooted knowledge, experience or even be irreverent towards any doctor. A decade ago, the stalwarts of the profession viewed me as irreverent and nothing but a glamour doll overcoming boredom from household chores. Women oftentimes are perceived in a particular way culturally. I learnt to never refute, rebut or waste time on challenging opinions. As I helped, cured and transformed the health of babies, mothers, families, it took the first five years to recognize the need for a lactation and nutrition educator for maternity. Soon it followed the nods of acknowledgement, approval and greetings from the above mentioned fraternity. Finally, a decade into this space, my same desire to assist people, my ability to be fit and presentable is viewed with admiration and respect. A senior doctor once said that without their promotion I will fizzle out within months. Today he is one of the many who has amicably dissolved this view and understood the serious, diligent yet ever improving work that I do. Dr. Santosh Agarwal (renowned pediatrician) congratulated me. He mentioned an infant who was hospitalized and in spite of all the tests they were unable to resolve the issue.  Invariably the rested and happy mother came back to his clinic post resolution. He was pleasantly surprised that she had undergone nutritional counseling with me.', 'There are three clear areas of my social impact in the last 11 years: lactation support, infant feeding, and health transformation. Medical professionals and maternity clients alike know what a lactation and maternity wellness specialist is and the need for one. Many gynecologists and pediatricians now actively have a lactation specialist, nutritionist and counselor on their team to guide mothers. This is a change I have engendered working relentlessly with mothers as there was a huge gap in breastfeeding information and awareness, and the need for mental health counseling postpartum. Postnatal blues and depression is a common mental health distress faced by new moms and in many cases it can destroy the childbirth experience for the entire family. Mothers need constant handholding and support which my postnatal program provides by combining nutrition, mental health counseling and lactation support. I am the pioneer in Kolkata for this combined Maternity Wellness Program and can now say that very few practitioners in India have created such a program. \r\nInfant weaning is a time that brings many challenges, questions and anxieties in mothers. My Infant Wellness Program offers customized solutions to weaning, bridging the gap between traditional weaning and modern baby led weaning techniques. This is the only such comprehensive weaning, developmental milestone and maternal counseling support available in the city.\r\nAs a Health Transformation Coach, a unique blend of Ayurvedic nutrition, mindfulness practices, and healing have transformed client behaviors, hormonal imbalances and diseases in a permanent way. My holistic approach is practically non-existent in India as most practitioners are either just a nutritionist, or healers or counselors. This combination is my offering to transform lives.', 'Books and food are a great combination for outreach and expansion. My latest offering is a book: Growing up with Superfoods. I am co authoring the book with a food writer and restaurateur focused on infant and child nutrition. This book aims to be complete with age based meal plans, recipes for the Indian palette. We are including nutritional content in over 80 recipe offerings. We hope to make it a fun yet informative resource with the USP of bar codes linking to short videos for each recipe.\r\nIn the maternity wellness arena, I have partnered with California based company, The Stroller Club, to bring forth classes on the global platform. The first step is blending Ayurveda hacks for a calm and sickness free pregnancy, Bharatnatyam steps for body balance, and sound vibrational therapy to stay anxiety free while you are expecting. We plan to expand the online tutorial mode and offer specialized classes for a global audience incorporating my varied knowledge bank.', 'Prevention is better than cure. Plant based nutrition can reverse Cancer and Diabetes. Most diseases have a psychosomatic origin in the human brain tied to subconscious and genetic information. I offer a health transformation practice that investigates the subconscious patterns of self sabotaging behavior. This is a holistic approach to reversing disease. Stress has become fashionable and so has having a nightlife. Hormonal imbalance and obesity is on the rise. We follow the biological clock when we sleep on time and wake up early. We respect nature when we are on a plant based diet. We do no self harm nor do we comfort eat if we forgive and embrace everyone in our lives. These are three simple corrections to perfect health: living based on the circadian rhythms, eating seasonal, local, cultural produce and work towards self awareness. One’s good health is the greatest gift of all. It is my pleasure and duty to restore health and bring this gift into all the lives I touch.', '[{"download_link":"files/g77EQDwGqYVpCxe7olCGVAtkYA2SCnYXyBBGaPSN.jpg","original_name":"7667e2ae66d8d05bf15722661a903202.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/ddiA3GO2fs0IccEbCyKLAT5v1kuAm4YefirouXRz.mp4","original_name":"Vidhi Disease Reversal 1.mp4"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/SMh116WjiS3jfDzHPKpGsxODBMUh7YcLhcIjAkXw.jpg","original_name":"t2 feature.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/pZYZbbKdtfhgOnN7fOnSx2NS5HkAWQu4k7ergRR7.pdf","original_name":"Testimonials 1 (1).pdf"}]', NULL, '2021-11-05 11:11:39', '2021-11-05 11:11:39', NULL, 0),
	(32, 6, 'N', 'Creative Arts (Art & Photography)', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'NEHA JAIPURIA', '1983-02-21', '9831167770', 'OLIVE.KOLKATA@GMAIL.COM', '198 A, BLOCK "J", NEW ALIPORE, KOLKATA - 700053', 'www.oliveinteriordesigners.com', 'https://www.facebook.com/OliveInteriorDesigners/', 'https://Instagram.com/oliveinteriordesigner/', 'https://www.facebook.com/OliveInteriorDesigners/', 'https://Instagram.com/oliveinteriordesigner/', 'Hi I am Neha Jaipuria,I am the Chief designer and founder of OLIVE and have been thriving in the world of interiors since 2004. Gaining expertise in business, I completed my studies in 2005, chose a career in design and have not looked back ever since. \r\nI am an avid traveller and gather inspiration and ideas throughout the surroundings, whether its a walk in the woods,or a trip to the supermarket. I find shapes, colours and imagery to inspire wherever I go. This ability to experience the world and draw it into work is phenomenally rewarding.\r\n   \r\nAmbitious, meticulous, creative and passion for design are qualities which make me achieve excellent outcome on my design sites. All designs at the OLIVE are based on research and experimentation with adaptability as the key factor. The focus is always on the site, context, the constraints and the opportunity that a project presents.  \r\nOur motto is what drives us –   Work hard and stay humble', 'OLIVE', 'PRINCIPAL DESIGNER', '17', '2021-06-30', '198 A, BLOCK \'J\' NEW ALIPORE', 'KOLKATA', 'WEST BENGAL', '700053', '9831167770', 'OLIVE.KOLKATA@GMAIL.COM', 'www.oliveinteriordesigners.com', NULL, 'I am able to pursue interesting high quality work that has a positive impact. Delivered inspired, efficient interior designs for commercial and residential markets. Exceeded specs for hundred satisfied clients. Created high-quality designs efficiently in a fast-paced environments. As far as achievement I am being able to maintain a happy and healthy family life as well as my career, I am able to handle challenge, complexity and change also able to exercise leadership, authority and influence. I have been able to secure award, growth and other acknowledgement of achievements.  I believe in celebrating every success or milestone and enjoy the journey and not lookout for the goal only. Every completed project and happy satisfied client is my success that\'s vey close to me.', 'The interior design industry is ever-growing. Despite this growth, there are challenges, From handling your clients to completing a project right on time, from getting the right kind of products to arranging the logistics, every little thing needs to be absolutely in place to gain a standard place in the market. Creative minds, hard-working and efficient manpower, right set of tools, and amazing products are keys to a successful project completion with flying colours.\r\nWe are busy people with too many things to deal with. In this scenario, it is a herculean task to ensure that every little thing related to a project is accomplished as per the given deadline. Managing the manpower involved in a project, making sure of the designs, dealing with the finances, handling the client, and not to mention the other formalities and official work! Finding the right mix of people in your team is the key. We have experts dealing with all the creative needs for the completion of a project. Our team is well-equipped to take care of your requirements.\r\nClients can be very demanding at times. Be it completing your project at a lesser time, or asking for personalised designs and products, and of course constraining the budget We are proud to be associated with creative geniuses – the craftsmen and artisans of our country, who excel in producing different handcrafted furniture. Needless to say, we ensure that the quality and design are as per the client expectations and within their budget. \r\nIt becomes very difficult to find the right people for the right kind of job especially when it comes to making customised interior design. Here again, our artists are the key for successful completion of your project.', 'The interior design field has embraced a role in improving the lives of people - locally, nationally, and globally. There are several challenges that make interior design an activity developed by professionals in the field. Basically, it is a way to transform the lives of people who live or enjoy a certain space, improving their quality of life in this through design and decoration. Our work is meant to improve quality of life. Our surroundings have an enormous impact on the way we behave and feel, and our role is more important than ever as we retreat to our homes during COVID-19. As a designer we resolve the functionality of a space and address scale, curate a desirable aesthetic, inject soul and tell a story for the inhabitants as well as effecting productivity. We evoke happiness and soothe the soul. It can inspire confidence, empathy, pride, creativity, security and energy. Creating a meaningful space that fulfils the needs of the inhabitant and optimizes their space is one of our key roles as designers and is essential to our society. It’s not about whether the walls are painted in the latest colours, but rather whether the space evokes the desired emotions in the user. I think that it is essential in order to create a sense of well-being in the home, to put together interiors where one can find oneself again and to create suitable spaces. The therapeutic role of interior architecture consists in creating well-being while representing the client’s ideas in material form. If this is done well, the clients are very happy because they recognize themselves in the interior architect’s work. We do everything we can to create the client’s universe, and this is a form of therapy.', 'I plan to provide designers with efficiencies that help them do more designing rather than the operations, communications, tracking, order management, and other stuff that has historically made up 75 percent of their job.\r\nOnce reserved largely for the wealthy, interior design services are gradually becoming available to almost everyone, A trend that will strengthen in the years ahead. Your budget won\'t determine whether you can have a home you like or not. There will be a solution for everyone, at every budget category.\r\nI wish to use fewer resources, the ability to complete the projects efficiently and smoothly, sometimes ahead of time, allows us to explore creative options to go the extra mile. Hence, the smooth collaboration, quick feedback, and holistic oversight will help us to soar to take our projects to new creative heights.\r\nFurthermore, will like to study, research and incorporate the sustainable way of designing, minimizing the harmful affects of construction material on human health and environment.', 'I like to boast that from the past 17 years of my career have been heading an all women team. This is my little way to help the society and women to be financially independent, encourage and mentor towards confidently facing the world both in work and personal life.', '[{"download_link":"files/OhgLDpTbD2AjWiLKAfbF79O7qZRSTD7Dotv8NQvQ.jpg","original_name":"WhatsApp Image 2021-11-05 at 11.48.34 PM.jpeg"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/ouHtJG0DzgclIpdtGPGaq9M9Tn8M8Vsxf5gXQ2xm.jpg","original_name":"WhatsApp Image 2021-11-05 at 10.48.26 PM (3).jpeg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/dyks06xWZ4K9m7CI7dLJa00RPNGzgLtEKv8iX0Zx.png","original_name":"Testimonial 1.png"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/UkWNvOBZK2hb71nzFxdPaPKz1M8BHcBY1IL52y3P.jpg","original_name":"WhatsApp Image 2021-11-05 at 10.48.26 PM (1).jpeg"}]', '2021-11-05 22:21:33', '2021-11-05 22:21:33', NULL, 0),
	(33, 3, 'Y', 'Enterprise', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Uzma Firoz', '1988-03-31', '9830836837', 'feroz_uzma@yahoo.com', 'p-15 metropolatian society kolkata 105', 'uzma_m_firoz', 'https://www.facebook.com/feroz.uzma', 'https://instagram.com/uzma_m_firoz?utm_medium=copy_link', NULL, 'https://instagram.com/style_addict_official?utm_medium=copy_link', 'Hello !\r\nThis Is Uzma Firoz founder of the famous jewellery brand STYLE ADDICT!\r\nI loved styling jewelleries since my teenage so this gave me a light in my career of jewellery field, I started my brand 7 years ago from my very small scale exhibtion! \r\nNow ,my brand is well known in kolkata, my brand has been featured in t2 , indulge , akhbar e mashriq etc\r\nWe are associated with with tolly celebrities & they are clients too \r\nour instagram fam is 40k+ \r\nWe did fashion shows , exhibtions , sponsored events and many more these years!', 'Style Addict', 'Owner', '7', '2021-06-30', 'p-115 metropolatian society kolkata 105', 'kolkata', 'westbengal', '700105', '9830836837', 'feroz_uzma@yahoo.com', NULL, 'https://www.instagram.com/invites/contact/?i=1ocxwja1llhao&utm_content=ie7kasi', 'Because of my business i started mixing with people which i thought i was not capable of !\r\nTalking to karigars , manufacturers.  handling my accounts alone was quite a tough job , still its tough i am learning only till now!\r\n\r\nAnd one should know what your clients will need !\r\nYour collections has to be updated!\r\n\r\nMy brand is loved by my clients because of we maintain quality, we customise accordingly as per client needs !\r\n\r\nI would say achievements would be not my award but i am known by my brand! \r\n\r\nI am invited in various fashion shows , award shows because of my brand!', 'I started with a box of jewellery it was really a tough job ,funds are really important for any work,but i was honest with my self that i won’t ask my husband for any fund or help, so it was really tough for my business!', 'Coming from a muslim background and working was a big deal , now lot of ladies in our (biradri) look up to me in my society, lot of women are working, almost 50% woman are working!', NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/T1jPFU7ysLisJOPJTnK9XJYvIH92ZopuAKQwCiZs.jpg","original_name":"CC80F6E1-7255-48DE-820E-8A45EA32A289.jpeg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-06 22:18:02', '2021-11-06 22:18:02', NULL, 0),
	(34, 3, 'N', 'Enterprise', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Vanita Bajoria', '1978-09-22', '9432335967', 'vanita@lodkolkata.com', 'Kamalalaya centre  156A, Lenin sarani 4th floor  Room no - 401 Kolkatta', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/vanita.bajoria', 'https://www.instagram.com/vanitabajoria/', 'https://www.facebook.com/lotdkolkata', 'https://www.instagram.com/lordofthedrinkskolkata/', NULL, 'Lord Of The Drinks', 'Director', '6', '2021-06-30', 'Fourth floor, South City Mall Kolkata, West Bengal, India 700068', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700068', '9831638079', 'vanita@lodkolkata.com', NULL, NULL, 'Learning is an ever-going process and personally what I feel is that one can learn and achieve anything with true dedication and devotion towards their dream. My key achievement would be that I step into an industry that is full of glamour and yet I stand strong on my moral grounds.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/83tPGxNMn3rs8r92wCY1sXfqm4mdjZkn107DNlOZ.jpg","original_name":"10518830_849033231795738_4309154143207765390_n.jpg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-08 15:44:01', '2021-11-08 15:44:01', NULL, 0),
	(35, 3, 'N', 'Enterprise', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Aradhita Kedia & Devanshi Chitlangia', '1993-01-08', '9831198024', 'aradhita.agarwal@gmail.com', '15b ballygunge park road, kedia sadan, kedia sadan', NULL, NULL, NULL, '@chaikaofficial', '@chaika.in', 'Aradhita Kedia is a graduate of Economics from the National University of Singapore (NUS). She has also studied Political Science and Economics at Sciences Po in France. Upon graduation she worked as a Interest Rate Swaps trader with BNP Paribas in Singapore and then moved back to work with her family business that is in the field of tea: Ellenbarrie and Karala Valley Tea Estates. She is also an experienced tea taster. In her free time she enjoys running, reading and trying out different cuisines.\r\n\r\nDevanshi Chitlangia has a dual major in Economics and Finance from Singapore Management University. She also studied entrepreneurship at Babson college, USA for a semester. Post her graduation, she worked as a portfolio analyst with Cambridge Associates in Singapore and soon left the same to work for her family tea estates- Panbari and Hoograjuli Tea. In her free time she enjoys food, fitness and travelling.', 'Chaika', 'Co-founder of chaika', '5', '2021-06-30', '3A, RIPON STREET', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700016', '9831198024', 'info@chaika.in', 'www.chaika.in', NULL, 'Our biggest achievement thus far has been being incubated by IIM Bangalore. Our start up was initially accepted in the Launchpad programme by IIM, followed by which we got incubated. This was a great honour for us, and we were especially proud to be recognized by a national stalwart like IIM Bangalore. \r\nA close second would be securing stalls at IPL and the T20 World Cup which is going on in Dubai. This resulted in global recognition for our brand. We are also very proud of managing to start our exports at the time of Covid when the world was absolutely closed up, and also maintaining a positive cash flow as a growing start up. Unlike most start ups which have a burn rate, we are actually cash flow positive, and sustaining our growth through our own revenues instead of further capital injections. \r\nOur key learnings have been determination to do the best no matter what and to have a flexible outlook, as things don\'t always work according to plan! We have learnt the importance of maintaining relationships - both with vendors and our own team. Clean and crisp communications help while doing the above. Lastly and most importantly, is maintaining a good relation with your co-founder as the two of us are the heart and soul of this brand !', 'Being female entrepreneurs in the male dominated manufacturing industry was not easy. Initially, our biggest challenge was dealing with manufacturers, local printers, packagers and vendors. We were subject to comments such as, Get your Father/ Husband along! We were often taken for a ride with payment terms, timelines and amounts. Soon, we learned how to firmly negotiate and get the respect we deserved. \r\n\r\nStarting off independently with an initial investment of just Rs.2 lakh, our challenge was to not only launch but also grow the business. We worked strategically, targeting the gifting market to maximise cash flow and also generate brand awareness. \r\n\r\nWhen Covid-19 hit us, it was initially very hard as a bulk of our sales were from wedding planners, travellers, hotels and clubs. Being a startup it was difficult to sustain our fixed expenses while in lockdown. We held on, we pivoted, we started marketing ourselves as the perfect covid solution, and got the essential service tag.  We started selling bulk packs of 100 sachets and 1kg packs for vending machines to corporations. We realised that offices were short staffed and would no longer be comfortable with calling the dhaba wala to give tea to their employees. We even sold a lot to households. This enabled Chaika even as a start-up to not bleed money during the lockdown months.', 'During the Covid months just after Amphan, despite being in a precarious situation we collected money for house rebuilding post the destruction of Amphan. Twenty houses were rebuilt with our donation. We also donated Chaika sachets for food packets distributed for Covid patients and their families through the NGO Ek Packet Ek Umeed.  \r\n\r\nChaika aims to promote the history, culture and heritage of India through its products. All elements are 100%  made in India - promoting Indianness through our packaging, feel and process. We strive to make Indianness fun, quirky and cool especially among the younger generations. \r\n\r\nWe are a 90% women team, with the policy of hiring women first. As both founders are women, we are aware of the challenges and obstacles facing women on a day to day basis when it comes to work. We are striving to make it a more inclusive work environment, and we try to fill as many vacancies with women as possible.', 'Chaika has grown to a worldwide brand in less than 2 years. From starting with a Rs.2 lakh investment, we now are selling online through e-commerce channels, are available in modern trade stores such as Foodhall and have even entered select premium General trade stores all around India. We are exporting to Singapore, Russia  and Dubai. We even had stalls at the recent IPL/ World Cup.\r\n\r\nIn the future, we are looking to expand our retail presence in India. We have been in talks with stalwarts such as Natures Basket, Spencers etc and have already got approval for the products. Moreover, we would want to gradually increase our general trade presence in India and make Chaika into a household brand.  \r\n\r\nThe bulk of our sales currently comes from exports, hence we are looking to participate in international trade fairs once the covid scenario is better to expand our foreign footprint. We are currently present in UAE, Singapore and Russia and are keen to explore other territories, especially ones with a large NRI presence such as the USA, UK and Australia. \r\n\r\nWe are also looking to expand our product line with a range of chai time snacks. The snacks too would follow our USP of being healthy, tasty, inherently Indian and convenient.', 'Chaika is an instant tea premix company that makes masala chai in less than 10 seconds. It is like the Tang for Masala Chai where all one has to do is empty out the contents of a sachet into a mug, add hot water, stir and it\'s ready! We have now diversified our product line with a range of instant iced teas which dissolve directly in cold water and are in the process of launching a range of tea time snacks. The idea for chaika started when we were working in Singapore. We craved masala chai but didnt know how to make it. Even when we tried, we failed! Moreover, the process took 15-20 minutes - we just didn\'t have the time in the morning! This thought made us leave our finance jobs to take the entrepreneurship route. Devanshi and Aradhita are part of families that have been in the tea business for over 70 years and we have both worked there to get a first hand experience of the industry. Aradhita is also a certified Tea Taster. We realised other professionals, students, travellers and corporate office staff must be facing the same issue. We also realised that people were switching over, from masala chai, the beverage they grew up with, to green tea or coffee, merely for the sake of convenience! This is what made us want to launch masala teas into a more convenient format!', '[{"download_link":"files/7BBjBBafsdefmxJB5hLbxYuk0ElnM1JpRZoAQ0KP.jpg","original_name":"20200924_111232.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/WKDNCpRE8VtB6xhi0TIBoJ9uJxdIUfa8UiSwXvtn.mp4","original_name":"Bombay Cutting Final.mp4"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/AwgrJJ78h9qb53rKq2Iyin3sOXdJf4J8ky36yQTZ.jpg","original_name":"indian express.jpeg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/HNPycA6H920e1m6fKCfT4woKFuCMNkvpNXkLm2jr.jpg","original_name":"dainik vishwamitra.jpeg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/u70lTHcN18ZnpjC9l4Gr8WdYIv3gLa7vIK7LKkmy.docx","original_name":"list of features.docx"}]', '2021-11-09 12:21:49', '2021-11-09 12:21:49', NULL, 0),
