	(37, 3, 'N', 'Enterprise', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Roshni Aditya', '1992-03-21', '9830310510', 'roshni@adityagroupindia.org', '182 amarpalli dum dum', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/roshni.dhir.18', 'https://www.instagram.com/roshni_aditya/', 'https://www.facebook.com/adityagroupindia', 'https://www.instagram.com/adityagroupofindia/?fbclid=IwAR0fouRmPwq77cvvizRiZwUaXTWvP8Qr6Cn-fk3m9JYFki_P8iL6nvU8OjQ', 'Mrs. Roshni Aditya, the Managing Director of Aditya Group has the primary role of controlling and directing the company’s resources and looking into the retention and recruitment of the required types and numbers of employees. She looks into the training and development phase of all staff members and ensures they work towards achieving common company objectives and missions. Other responsibilities include developing strategic plans to attain company goals, planning cost-effective operations and market development activities, assuming accountability for the company operations all while building and maintaining an effective team.', 'ADITYA GROUP', 'Managing Director', '8', '2021-06-30', '965, jessore road, kolkata 700055', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700055', '9830310510', 'roshni@adityagroupindia.org', 'https://adityagroupindia.org/', NULL, 'She is an integral part of the Managing Committee of Bhaskar Aditya Foundation (BAF) and the Dum Dum Aditya Educational Society. As such, she contributes to the overall quality of the units by developing efficient teams and reviewing, employing and recommending improved procedures and policies. Her inspiring, passionate and forward-thinking leadership skills allow her to develop and execute business strategies to attain long- and short-term goals. She is responsible for overseeing the day-to-day business operations as well as financial performance and ensuring all of the legal guidelines and company policies are clearly communicated and adhered to. Under the umbrella of BAF, she carries out various CSR activities while developing strategic operating plans. She also directs and supervises the activities of the principals and management staff of the School Board and liaisons with the board to ensure all of the efforts are in alignment with strategies for attaining goals.', NULL, 'Under the umbrella of Bhaskar Aditya Foundation, she carries out various CSR activities while developing strategic operating plans. She also directs and supervises the activities of the principals and management staff of the School Board and liaisons with the board to ensure all of the efforts are in alignment with strategies for attaining goals. \r\nVarious scholarships are given out to school and sports students under this Foundation to help nurture grassroot talent.', 'A leader and strategist, she is able to steer the company in the most profitable direction while ensuring the company’s mission, vision and long-term goals are met. Additionally, she is responsible for analysing problematic situations and offer solutions for company growth and survival. She has successfully built and managed a diverse group of employees and works towards achieving company growth targets and projections in a competitive and dynamic environment. \r\nOur future plans include the expansion of all our hospitality outlets to various parts of the city along with nurturing the concept of Amar Paray Amar School wherein Aditya Academy is planning to tie-up with pre-schools to be their Authorised Pre-Schooling Partner, wherein kids after completion of pre-schooling can join Aditya Academy for Junior & high school experience. It will come up with 100 preschools, covering every nook & corner of the city.', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/JSoYNXMiLOPQ8tsj1RKkL8kmplWsxGhWB4NSZKWU.jpg","original_name":"WhatsApp Image 2021-11-09 at 19.42.10.jpeg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/klaLhbWxeYjjoGRQy2iZNw7EMZMbaroVPk1UjSQP.pdf","original_name":"Roshni Mam Profile.pdf"}]', '2021-11-09 19:12:30', '2021-11-09 19:12:30', NULL, 0),
	(38, 5, 'N', 'Sports', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'RIDHI BAHETY', '2002-07-18', '9831343433', 'ridhibahety@gmail.com', 'P-217, cit scheme 7 M, Kolkata-700054', NULL, 'rekha bahety', 'Ridhi_bahety_', NULL, NULL, 'I\'m very passionate about sports since my childhood. From when I was young I used to play a number of sports like Table Tennis, Swimming, Athletics along with Skating. Infact I was a district champion in Table Tennis, a state level swimmer and a State Champion in Skating. \r\nBut as I started growing up I realised that it was Skating that I was most passionate about and I loved it from all my heart. I realised that it was not just a hobby for me but that it meant much more. Ever since I have wanted to win a medal for my state and take West Bengal\'s name high at the National Level. \r\nApart from sports I am also enthusiastic about dancing. I had started dancing at the age of 4 and at 15 I was the appointed the Junior Choreographer at Jhankar Dance Center. I also enjoy reading in my free time as it helps calm me down and makes me feel relaxed and at ease.', 'BSU SKATING ACADEMY', 'National medalist', '12', '2021-06-30', 'Bidhan Sisu udyan, CIT ROAD, SCHEME 7 M,', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700054', '9804221906', 'victorbalmiki@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'From the age of 7 I started participating in the State Level Skating Championships. \r\n\r\nAt the age of 8 I won my first State Championship and participated in the National Skating Championship held at Bangalore, Karnataka.\r\n\r\nEver since then I have won a total of 12 Golds, 11 Silvers and 6 Bronze medals at the State Championship. \r\n\r\nI have won a total of 8 Golds, 1 Silver and 1 Bronze at the East Zone Skating Championships.\r\n\r\nAt the National Level I have won 6 Golds, 6 Silvers and 2 Bronze medals winning a total of 14 medals at the National level.\r\n\r\nHere are the details of my achievements in the last 4 years :\r\n\r\n2017\r\n\r\n\r\nCBSE Far East Zone Skating competition held at Raipur \r\n\r\n300mt-Gold\r\n\r\n500mt-Gold\r\n\r\n\r\nCBSE National Skating competition held at Bhopal\r\n\r\n300mt-4th\r\n\r\n500mt-4th\r\n\r\n\r\nWest Bengal State Skating Championship\r\n\r\n300mt-Gold\r\n\r\n500mt-Gold\r\n\r\n1000mt-Gold\r\n\r\n3000mt-Gold\r\n\r\n\r\n2018\r\n\r\n\r\nCBSE Far East Zone Skating competition held at Raipur\r\n\r\n300mt-Gold\r\n\r\n500mt-Gold\r\n\r\n\r\nCBSE National Skating competition held at Raipur\r\n\r\n300mt- Silver\r\n\r\n500mt-Gold\r\n\r\nSchool Games Federation of India National Championship held at Belgaum from 27th to 31st 2018- \r\n\r\nRoad 3km -Gold \r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nRoller Skating Federation of India National Championship held at Vishakhapatnam - \r\n\r\n4th\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n2019\r\n\r\n\r\nAll India Open National Championship held at Noida from 18th to 21st April 2019 - \r\n\r\n1 lap - Gold\r\n\r\n1000m - Gold\r\n\r\n3000m - Gold\r\n\r\n\r\nCBSE Far East zone held at Raipur from 12th to 14th October2019 -\r\n\r\n300m- Gold\r\n\r\n500m - Gold\r\n\r\n\r\nCBSE National Skating Competition held at Belgaum from 27th to 30th November-\r\n\r\n300m- Bronze\r\n\r\n500m- Silver\r\n\r\nSchool Games federation of India National Championship held at Belgaum from 27th to 31st November 2019- \r\n\r\n4th\r\n\r\n\r\nRoller Skating Federation of India National Championship held at Visakhapatnam From 15th to 23rd December-\r\n\r\nSilver\r\n\r\n\r\nNational Ranking Championship held at Noida from 5th to 8th October 2019- \r\n\r\n1 Lap- Silver \r\n\r\n500m - Silver\r\n\r\n3000m - Gold\r\n\r\n\r\nMy name was published in India Book of Records 2020 for achievements in Skating as I was the first and only person from West Bengal to achieve medals at all the major national events in Speed Skating .', 'The biggest challenge in my career as a skater from West Bengal was lack of proper infrastructure for Skating. The races at the National Level took place on a 200m banked tracks which are elliptical tracks sloped at the turns. There is not a single such track in West Bengal because of which we had to practise on road and that made it really difficult for us to compete with our competitors from different states who would have year round practise on banked tracks. Also due to heavy traffic in the city we had to start practise on the road as early as 4am because later a lot of cars kept coming on the roads which made it very dangerous to skate there. \r\n\r\nI overcame this challenge by travelling to various states for practising on banked track. I would attend camps conducted by some of India\'s best skaters to understand how to use the banked track. It was obviously not the same as practising on a proper track all year but as we say where there\'s a will, there\'s a way. In this case where there\'s a *wheel* there\'s a way!', 'Skating in not a very popular sport in West Bengal. For many years people used to think that it is almost impossible for someone from West Bengal to win a medal at the National level Skating championships. But after winning my first medal at the National championship a lot of skaters got encouraged to train hard and started targetting the Nationals. What had once been considered to be unachievable had become a goal for many of my fellow skaters.\r\n\r\nAlso, even though we call ourselves a modern society, a lot of people still believe that sports is not something meant for girls, especially a super fast sport like skating where you can fall down and get major injuries and scars. A lot of such people were surprised that it was a girl and not a boy who had achieved the first medal for West Bengal.\r\nSo in a small way I feel my work has positively impacted the society.', 'Like every athlete, it\'s my dream to represent my nation, to bear the tricolour. My future plan is to train hard, go for the Indian Team trials and get selected in the National Team. I want to win medals at the Asian games and the world championship for my country.\r\n\r\nAlong with this I\'m currently pursuing Economic Honours from St. Xavier\'s University as well as Financial Risk Management of which I have cleared the first level.\r\nSo I would complete the FRM degree along with my graduation after which I would like to do an MBA from a top management College.\r\n\r\nI really want to break this stereotype that one can either be good in academics or in sports by striking a balance between both', 'I would just like to say that Skating does not get as much recognition as other sports even though it requires as much hardwork, skill, determination and patience to play. In my opinion all sports deserve the same respect and recognition and I would be very grateful if this platform helps in promoting this sport in our State and helps it receive the respect it deserves.', '[{"download_link":"files/b0gCg0aJAJ8eVivxaIYuhEt7v4a3iIyim7Sa33S7.jpg","original_name":"AA5BF911-46C5-4ABA-920B-FF26B9FC83FA.jpeg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/1yOjAHBnuhVSVv2HW9BlSmTbVHsiEi2toT8e8OxH.mov","original_name":"trim.782FE8C4-F392-49D1-89E6-5DD451C34051.MOV"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/6j5eZCExJNSWO3BSCrhjj5k24U2rqj7f53c4fHlT.zip","original_name":"new doc 2020-07-21 19.41.04.zip"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/hjT72ROcqzOXrOqzVoNj30iW9uWXYatB07JrAr3d.pdf","original_name":"new doc 2021-11-10 23.46.28.pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/v4Qy4uI38N9m8EA0s8pLbBCrTgdMwB9qW8F9PfWD.pdf","original_name":"new doc 2021-11-11 00.56.35.pdf"}]', '2021-11-11 00:30:25', '2021-11-11 00:30:25', NULL, 0),
	(39, 8, 'N', 'Literary', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Dr. Priyasi Das', '1999-11-13', '9007715758', 'priyasidas15@gmail.com', '175/4, R.N. Guha Road, Landmark - Masjid Gate, Kolkata - 700028', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/authorpriyasi/', 'https://www.instagram.com/priyasi_das', 'https://www.instagram.com/priyaswisdompublication', NULL, 'Dr. Priyasi Das belongs from the City of Joy Kolkata. She is an Award Winning Author, Engineer, Publisher, Honorary Doctorate in Literature, Multiple Record Holder, Guinness World Record (Mass Attempt Holder) & MISS E&E Universe (West Bengal). She has Authored 8 Books & Co Authored more than 48 Anthologies. She is the founder of Priya\'s Wisdom Publication. Priyasi is a well known author for her 8 Literary Masterpieces. She completed her research & thesis in Literature & got her HONORARY DOCTORATE DEGREE in Literature from GLOBAL TRIUMPH VIRTUAL UNIVERSITY. She has achieved multiple National & World records for being the first person to write a Reality based book on COVID-19. She has been awarded with INDIA BOOK OF RECORDS, VAJRA WORLD RECORDS, OMG BOOK OF RECORDS, GLOBAL RECORDS RESEARCH & FOUNDATION, MVLA GLOBAL ACHIEVERS AWARD, LAUREATE AWARD & many others.', 'Priya\'s Wisdom Publication', 'Founder', '5', '2021-06-30', '175/4, R.N. Guha Road', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700028', '9123062719', 'priyaspublication@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'I started writing since I was 10 years old. Nothing stopped me to portray my emotions via writing. Writing has been the essence & beauty of calmness to me. I prepared my thesis & research on COVID-19 & achieved my Doctorate in Literature with my knowledge & capability. I became a National & World Record Holder for being the "First Women to write a Reality based book on COVID-19." \r\n\r\nFew of my Achievements -\r\n1. India Book of Records\r\n2. Vajra World Records\r\n3. Global Records & Research Foundation\r\n4. OMG Book of Records\r\n5. Star Book of International Records\r\n6. Laureate Award\r\n7. Nari Samman Award\r\n8. Global Achievers Award\r\n9. Cherry Book Award\r\n10. Honorary Doctorate in Literature\r\n11. 100 Inspiring Authors of India\r\n12. Guinness World Record (Mass Attempt Holder)\r\n13. India Star Icon Award\r\n14. India Star Women Award\r\n15. Her Ka Hunar Award\r\n16. Influential Women Award\r\n17. 50 Inspiring Authors Award\r\n18. GrandsQueen Leadership Awards 2021\r\n19. REX Karamveer Chakra Award\r\n20. Pride of Nation (Pratibha Samman Award)\r\n21. Ne8x - Author of The Year 2020\r\n22. Author Pages - Best Women Writer Award\r\n23. ICMDR - Best Poetry Award (Nominee)\r\n24. India Star Republic Award\r\n25. India Star Diva - 2019\r\n26. Miss E&E Universe (West Bengal) - 2019\r\n27. Aaghaz 2K20 Author Awards\r\n28. Miss Beautiful Face - Kolkata', 'My biggest challenge in life was to publish my first book as I didn\'t had anyone to guide me. Publishing a book was not easy and there were several process to go through while publishing a book like formatting, editing & etc. I did all of it by myself without anybody\'s help. I feel glad that I trusted myself & my passion. Today I am an Entrepreneur & Author and I have my own Freelancing Publishing House i.e., PRIYA\'S WISDOM PUBLICATION', 'My work has created a changement in the world of Literature as I can proudly say that my initiative "PWP" is guiding & giving chance to the aspiring authors to bring out there talents with the power of pen. \r\n\r\nBy writing the reality based book on COVID-19 I got a huge positive response & it was Amazon Bestseller too at No. #27. It\'s a must read book for everyone.', 'I just want to help aspiring authors by guiding them with the best knowledge regarding Literature. And ofcourse I wish to write more reality based books for my readers.', '"From Appreciation we gain Inspiration!"\r\n\r\nWe should never loose hope. We should believe in our Capabilities & let our passion fly high. \r\n\r\nWRITE, READ, REPEAT!', '[{"download_link":"files/WwQ6bvD1Sz4IY59eC98xe391Ky5RqpO8FNblzP7d.jpg","original_name":"inbound3711828536981300862.jpg"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/PmumXdJpk5JM8ITZP2aKyrqvPCa6PNbyPk1Dbgpf.jpg","original_name":"inbound7404816143369449629.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/yEVO3e57ksPjfpWEz2CpmR7Scd4aFmLqTbq92SBg.jpg","original_name":"inbound2661653989661859810.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/bGKagSm3BcEMEfORn8wMp0GaPTFYh9tMBIkmJbRK.pdf","original_name":"inbound2826137033066642119.pdf"}]', '2021-11-12 10:18:42', '2021-11-12 10:18:42', NULL, 0),
	(40, 6, 'N', 'Creative Arts (Art & Photography)', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Moutushi Chakraborty', '1975-09-28', '9163749642', 'moutushi75@gmail.com', 'Flat# 1103, Tower 3, Mallika, Malancha Housing Complex, Street no. 622, Action Area 2B', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/moutushi.chakraborty.5', 'moutushi75', NULL, NULL, 'I am a practising Artist and Academician based in Kolkata. I have been teaching at the School of Fine-Arts, Amity University Kolkata since it\'s inception in 2015. Teaching has been my passion for many years as it gives me the opportunity to shape young minds, the future of India, the generation for whom nothing is impossible. I have been fortunate to study under great teachers at Kalabhavan-Santiniketan, M. S. University Baroda and Wimbledon School of Art (as Commonwealth Fellow & Charles Wallace awardee). It is my hope to share with my students the wisdom and knowledge I collected in life. I also inspire and encourage my students to engage in Community activities, where they share their knowledge with others. We have done Street Grafitti on Women\'s Day and Printmaking workshop for the Deaf Women of W. Bengal. It is my hope that my students will continue this cycle of Goodwill.', 'Amity University Kolkata', 'Assistant Professor', '19', '2021-06-30', 'Major Arterial Road(South-East), AA II, Rajarhat, Newtown, West Bengal 700135', 'NEW TOWN', 'West Bengal', '700135', '9163749642', 'mchakraborty@kol.amity.edu', 'https://www.amity.edu/kolkata/', NULL, 'As a 21st century Artist in Modern India I feel the biggest learning is that India is a powerhouse of culture, knowledge and skills passed down from rich heritage  across generations. We no longer need to look to the West or East to seek accreditation. It is time to nurture the homegrown talent and prepare leaders of the Future.', 'My first job in Delhi - an unknown city was my biggest challenge. It was my first instep into the Academic world. But the belief that I can make a difference in others\' lives kept me going. The challenge to bring updated knowledge to my students enthused me to overcome all obstacles with elan.', 'I believe my Artwork has brought solace to many a heart and mind by speaking of inner turmoils faced by women of all ages. I felt that it was important for women to join hands and draw strength from each other to create unprecedented milestones. This indeed has created miraculous achievements in my life and brought great many opportunities for good work.', 'It is my dream to see my students grow up to be stalwarts on their own, doing good for themselves and the society at large. I have always told them that sharing is the first step towards emancipation, as it not just brings strength to others but also to themselves. The more we share, the more we grow.', 'Support living artists. Help them create a difference to the society you live in. It does not cost much but brings the opportunity to add immeasurable value to lives, which cannot be measured in currency.', '[{"download_link":"files/7i4TaJ88CH0ilaRJ5a5zEB9d0Ubk0Iq3khce9FiZ.jpg","original_name":"IMG_20211105_003956.jpg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/YXCdBxUpe3AgOO0EBTaykN3x9EyqsSJ4yqMIaDqV.pdf","original_name":"Moutushi Chakraborty CV.pdf"}]', '2021-11-12 20:14:09', '2021-11-12 20:14:09', NULL, 0),
