	(42, 6, 'Y', 'Creative Arts (Art & Photography)', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Pooja Singh', '1983-12-12', '9163354452', 'pasingh.vrata@gmail.com', 'Manjula Apartments, Flat no- 3A, 3rd Floor, 367 Jodhpur, Jodhpur Park, Kolkata -68', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/vrata.co/', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/vrata.co/', NULL, 'I am Pooja Singh, an interior designer representing my company VRATA. \r\n\r\nVrata - means a solemn promise, it means \r\ndevotion a pledge.  \r\n\r\nVrata is a baby in the groove which has accomplished itself as a trustworthy and reputed establishments in the field of interior & exteriors within a very short span of time. \r\n\r\nWe started the company in the year 2015, towards a goal of having satisfied client on our esteemed client list. \r\n\r\nOur aim is to develop,design, and implement the most innovative yet cost effective solution for each project irrespective of the size, be it a fresh design or a redesign. \r\n\r\nWe specialise in customised, recycled and modular interior solutions. \r\n\r\nServices we provide are : \r\nResidential \r\nCommercial \r\nLandscaping designing. \r\n\r\nOur achievements - \r\n\r\nWe have bagged the award for best accessories by the jury members consisting of Mr.Vivek Singh Rathore of Salient Design Studios, in the year 2015.  \r\n \r\nIn the year 2018, I was featured  in Times of India \r\nfor the designing the Caffeteria Roastery located in 70B, Hindustan Park.  \r\n\r\nCurrently my ongoing project is for Craft Coffee which is are a huge coffee outlet where in we will be designing not just the flagship store but all the Kiosks and outlets across Kolkata. \r\n\r\nApart from this we have got several testimonies from our clients in Tea board, Genexx Valley, TFF gym in Garihat (Reliance Mall top floor and  Eastern chronicles,\r\n \r\nI want to reach out to any and every individual that never ever give up on your dreams if I can so can you ans give back to the Mother Nature as much as you can.', 'Vrata', 'Craft Coffee', '7', '2021-06-30', 'Vrata 50B, Ballygunge Circular Road, 1st Floor, Kol-19', 'Kolkata', 'West bengal', '700019', '9163354452', 'pssingh.vrata@gmail.com', 'https://www.facebook.com/vrata.co/', NULL, 'Team work and discipline. \r\nCovered by Times of India for Roastery.', 'My carpenters ditched me but still I delivered the project on time. \r\nI had a back up of the back up.', 'I have tried to minimise the use of wood to my best possibility, have always emphasised my clients to use and recycle.', 'Yes very soon I am entering the F&B industry with Craft Coffee for whom I am designing presently.', 'We all have that inbuilt creativity within us just let it flow for once in your life.', '[{"download_link":"files/O6Fxo8WG5WFMXyg5g4PDnUTvHL8jdanuAIC53jsX.jpg","original_name":"25A1542E-2B78-4FAF-AC1F-9466CE967925.jpeg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-12 23:23:01', '2021-11-12 23:23:01', NULL, 0),
	(43, 2, 'Y', 'Health & Wellness', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Reena Nair', '1960-11-09', '3366057624', 'reenanair2020@gmail.com', 'Tata Medical Center, 14 Main Arterial Road, (EW),, Newtown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'I did MB;BS and MD [Internal Medicine] Goa Medical College [1979-1988]\r\nfollowed by Medical Oncology Residency [1988-89] and Fellowship [1991-1994] at Tata \r\n   Memorial Hospital.\r\nI went on to become a Medical Oncology Faculty [Lecturer to Professor] at Tata Memorial Hospital, Mumbai   \r\n   from 1994 to 2012.\r\nI have been aPrincipal Investigator in 35 Clinical Trials [Investigator initiated as well as Industry   \r\n   sponsored trials]\r\nI  have been the Executive Committee Member and Faculty at Australia and Asia Pacific Clinical \r\n  Oncology Research Development (ACORD) Workshop since 2010 -2017.\r\nI have published over 125 papers and book chapters.\r\n\r\nMy current Interest is in management of Hematological malignancies.\r\nIam a Founding member of the Lymphoma Registry of Mumbai 2009 to 2012.\r\nI have been the Chairperson, Biobank oversee Committee, TMC, Kolkata 2016 till 2020.\r\nI have also been the Founding member of the National Myeloma Group [IMAGe] 2017 onwards, \r\nand Principal Investigator of the Onco-collect Lymphoma Registry 2018 onwards\r\nI have been Honoured with the Doctors Conclave award by Economic Times2020  \r\nin the category of  “Inspiring Oncologist of India”', NULL, 'Tata Medical Center', '35', '2021-06-30', 'Tata Medical Center, 14 Main Arterial Road, (EW),, Newtown', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700160', '3366057624', 'reena.nair@tmckolkata.com', NULL, NULL, 'I have trained in Medical Oncology and specialize in the treatment of Lymphomas and Leukemias. Working in the Government Hospital and not for profi Institutes taught me to look after the marginalized section of the population with empathy. I learnt to use resources judiciously and rose to the challenge of making curative treatments available to patients at any cost.\r\nI have been able to inspire my patients to give back to the society that helped them in the time of their needs. My patients donate generously through their NGOs towards treatment completion of new patients, making the standard of care treatment available for the marginalized patients and providing support in the form of counselling new patients go through the treatment. \r\nWe disseminate information to patients on therapy as well as those who have completed therapy through Patient Survivor day programs. \r\nI have been a teacher, mentor and guide to many Medical Oncologists across the country. Many of them are now in key positions in the Government as well as the private hospitals.\r\nI have collaborated and paricipated in research in Oncology for over 30 years and have over 150 papers published in Peer reviewed journals and in text books.', 'I was fortunate to be born in a progressive thinking family, where my education was given the first priority. I was taught by the convent nuns and dedicated teachers of Carmel Convent School in Durgapur to focus on building myself into a good citizen, with compassion for my fellow country men and women. I trained under the best minds in the field of Oncology in my formative years at the Tata Memorial Hospital in Mumbai. I was encouraged to work beyond my duty towards patient care and was initiated into clinical research and trials. I married a friend and colleague and received all the encouragement to achieve the best in my carrier.\r\nSo honestly I have not faced any challenges in achieving my goals.', 'Working with cancer patients with empathy, and finding solutions to many of their logistic and financial problems helped save lives of treatable/ curable cancer patients. I have encouraged my patient survivors and their care givers to initiate counselling groups, and fund raising for new patients with Lymphoma. This has enabled large number of otherwise unaffording patients receive the standard of care treatment for their disease. My patients run charities that enable new patients complete their treatment through the Lymphoma foundation I set up at the Tata Memorial Hospital, Mumbai; Akanksha Medical Trust, Pune; and Ashray, Kolkata.\r\nThese NGOs also take up counselling new Lymphoma patients in their initial difficult days of dealing with the diagnosis and understanding the inticacies of treatment.\r\nI have been instrumental in encouraging my younger colleagues train in clinical research methodologies. I have been a faculty and the Steering as well as the Executive Comittee member of the Australia and Asia Pacific Clinical Oncology Training Workshop for over a decade. This group has conducted a large number of workshops in different parts of the country over the last few years in order to bring awareness in the younger oncology community regarding the most scientific methods to evaluate new treatments, understand their true impact and use them judiciously.', 'Iam working with the new technologies, specially digital in order to make infromation available to patients. One such experiment is the Lymphomap platform recently launched. Not only will it provide information but also expertise to patients and their doctors in remote areas. Making treatments uniform across the country through well written guidelines as well as  making treatment available close to the patients residence is my goal.\r\nWith the help of Machine learning and Artificial Intelligence, my recent work involves trying to understand treatment strategies that may make a difference in the long term outcomes of patients with a high risk of recurrence of their lymphoma/ cancer.', 'I was born in Durgapur, West Bengal to parents from North India, whose families had settled in New Delhi during partition. I trained and worked in Goa and Mumbai during my formative years, and married a friend and colleague from Kerala in South India. I am a complete Indian.', '[{"download_link":"files/OwxtdItx1obMBygalm08v5XjGUZpY8xiaqMu075a.jpg","original_name":"image001.jpg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-13 23:14:53', '2021-11-13 23:14:53', NULL, 0),
	(44, 2, 'Y', 'Health & Wellness', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'DR. SUSHMITA ROY CHOWDHURY', '1972-07-18', '9836967500', 'docsrc01@gmail.com', 'WL9, Sanjerva Town Bungalow Complex, Opposite Aquatica, New Town Kol- 700156', NULL, 'Sushmita RoyC', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Fortis Hospital Kolkata', 'Director Pulmonolovy', '18', '2021-06-30', 'Fortis Hospital Anandapur', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', NULL, '3366284040', 'docsrc@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'I started as a Pulmonologist in India who trained further in UK to return to Kolkata with new skills  to make it a world class destination in the field of Interventional Pulmonology. Covid times tested our mettle to the limits and my biggest achievement apart from looking after complicated respiratory patients has been to be able to serve the people of my city during a devastating pandemic of our life times. Each patient that went back to their family from hospital was the very reason I chose tbis profession and am proud to be a part of .', 'Challenges are a part of parcel in my profession and we overcome them with grit and hope . There have been too many to name one but the interesting one to recount will be when I chose Pulmonology as my specialisation, I was asked why I wouldn\'t want to be a gynaecologist . I had to convince and prove my passion for the subject inorder to persue it.', 'I have tried to do my best at work and help as many patients as I could. I have tried to instill the love of the subject in many juniors and am happy to see so many of them opting to be a Pulmonologist.', 'I hope to be able to be part of initiatives for upliftment of medical care in our part of the country .', 'No', '[{"download_link":"files/3rexelvD4S0kyUJxu21npEtvaIxeQJUiJIHf2EOs.jpg","original_name":"Screenshot_20211114-001253_Gallery.jpg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-14 12:01:58', '2021-11-14 12:01:58', NULL, 0),
	(45, 7, 'Y', 'Performing Arts (Music, Dance & Theatre)', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'anubha fatehpuria', '1976-07-28', '9830238909', 'anubhaf@gmail.com', '2a desaproya park east; 3rd floor; kolkata 700029', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/anubha.fatehpuria/', 'https://www.instagram.com/anubbhaafatehpuria/', NULL, NULL, 'AnubhaFatehpuria – an actor (since 1995) and a practicing architect (since 2001) – is the recipient of the Sangeet Natak Akademi’s prestigious Ustad Bismillah Khan Yuva Puruskar 2013-14, The Telegraph SHE Awards 2019 and Shyamal Sen Smriti Puraskar 2007 for her theatre acting. \r\nShe has worked with directors like Habib Tanveer, Shyamanand Jalan, Usha Ganguli, Rajinder Nath, Alyque Padamsee, Wlodzimierz Staniewski (Poland), Suman Mukhopadhyay, Vinay Sharma, Vikarm Iyengar, John Britton (UK), Purva Naresh, Tulika Das – only to name some. \r\nAnubha has received extensive theatre training from Late Shyamanand Jalan (2003-2010). She continues to learn the craft of acting and theatre-making under Vinay Sharma (actor, director, writer and scenographer) from 2006 onwards. \r\nAnubha has been Padatik Theatre Executive Co-director (2010–2016) and Core-group member/actor with Ranan Performance Collective (2002–2013). She is an actor with Padatik Theatre Kolkata since 2002 and is currently Director-Programmes there. \r\nShe has acted on screen for directors like Seema Pahwa, Prasoon Pandey, Aparna Sen, Shoojit Sircar, Aniruddha Roy Chowdhury, Atul Mongia, Anshai Lal, Bishnu D.Haldar, Anupam Misra, Kamlesh Soni, Vijay Veeraml & Marcel Odenbach (Germany).\r\n\r\nOver the years Anubha has had extensive and workshop training in - Fine Arts under a few artists including Arup Das (1990-96); Hindustani Classical Vocal under Padmashree Late Smt. Girija Devi and her student Smt. Mitali Sengupta (1990-02); Initial training in Bharatnayam Dance style under Sonal Mansingh (1986-88); Bharatnatyam from Kalamandalam (Kolkata) under Smt. Thankamani Kutty & Smt. Uma Venkat (1988-96); Basic training in Manipuri Dance under Smt. Preeti Patel (1994-96); Workshop training in Mohiniattam Dance style, Kalaripayattu and Thang Ta\r\n\r\nAs an architect – a recipient of the Nagpur University Gold Medal (2001) for Bachelors in Architecture, graduating from LAD and SRP College for Women (Nagpur), Anubha interned at Ar. Balkrishna V Doshi’s SANGATH (Ahmedabad) and after graduating she worked under Ar. Dulal Mukherjee (Kolkata) for a brief period of time till 2002. Practicing independently thereafter, Anubha was also an in-house consultant architect with a real estate firm in Kolkata from 2003 to 2011. She has been a visiting faculty for Design at the Architecture Dept. at Jadavpur University. Since 2011 she has been running her own design studio, now in association with Ar Richa Bose – currently working on projects which include performing arts centres, residences, cafes, clinic/wellness centres among others – in various cities. Their design studio has received several recognitions for green practices.', NULL, 'actor', '26', '2021-06-30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '9830238909', 'anubhaf@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/GMDcVFip4gJElSFgk7RCdJLdauft7sjk2ELifgxj.jpg","original_name":"anubha fatehpuria 2019.jpg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-14 22:33:10', '2021-11-14 22:33:10', NULL, 0),
	(46, 6, 'Y', 'Creative Arts (Art & Photography)', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Soma Bhowmik', '1988-08-09', '9933911605', 'somaart10@gmail.com', '1114/B, Prince Court, 4th Floor, Flat- D3, Prince Anwar Shah Road, Kolkata -700068', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/soma.bhowmik.3', 'https://instagram.com/bhowmiksoma?utm_medium=copy_link', 'https://www.facebook.com/SisterNiveditaUniversity/', 'https://instagram.com/sisterniveditauniversityindia', 'I have earned a Graduation (2012) and a Post-Graduation (2014) in History of Art from Kala Bhavana, Visva Bharati University, Santiniketan. Presently I am pursuing my PhD on Curatorial Possibilities in Contemporary Art from Visva Bharati University. My dissertation thesis on the Changing Iconography of Durga in the context of Urban Popular Culture has secured praiseworthy academic credit. My academic background in art & art history has made me a passionate art-historian, art curator and art writer focusing mostly on modern and contemporary art. I have taught art history as a Guest Faculty at Amity University, Kolkata and Government College of Art & Craft, Kolkata. I have curated several shows of modern and contemporary art in Kolkata and Delhi in association with various significant galleries and independently as well. I have curated shows of the heritage artists, senior artists as well as junior artists. Before joining Arts Acre Foundation I have worked as a curator in Maya Art Space and Emami Chisel Gallery thus acquiring a rich curatorial experience. I am a regular writer and art critic who has published several essays and reviews in different journals and art magazines both national and international. I was the associate editor of ArtEast Magazine (Kolkata) since 2015 and the former editor of a monthly journal Art Fact (Kolkata). I have written a monograph on the famous artist Hirendranath Dutta published by Rajya Charukala Parshad, Information and Culture Department, West Bengal Government. As the Director of Arts Acre Foundation, I have extended my expertise in Curatorial ventures and art history by conducting Art Appreciation courses, Seminars, Workshops and creating opportunities for increasing number of art viewers and art enthusiasts to visit the place and make the space vibrant. Presently I am Head of the Department of School of Fine Arts and Design, Sister', 'Sister Nivedita University', 'HOD, School of Fine Arts and Design', '2', '2021-06-30', 'DG Block(Newtown), Action Area I, 1/2, Newtown, New Town, West Bengal 700156', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700156', '7595044470', 'info@snuniv.ac.in', 'https://snuniv.ac.in/contact-us.aspx', 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCxcojVjhaHtM2vE0e6QBVmA', 'The key learnings of my career have been the teaching assignments and curatorial projects. Each and every teaching assignment for me has been also a learning moment for me as the communication with the students has to be improved and developed not only to bring clarity to the teaching content but also to reach out the students coming from diverse backgrounds. I realized, sooner than later, that teacher is a learner as every class is a fresh challenge. However, the sense of being awarded comes when I learn that my students have received the recognition they deserve.\r\nEach and every curatorial project too has been a learning experience for me as well. Usually there is no prototype to follow since each curatorial project, independent or commissioned, requires a fresh start. However, when a curated exhibition reaches the stage where the show assumes a meaningful status and is able to reach many viewers, I feel a sense of achievement. Especially when my curated show receives critical acclaim, good media review and also makes it commercially viable, I feel that is one of the key achievements in my career.', 'One of the biggest challenges I have faced in my career when I ventured to curate shows with young and unknown artists. It is extremely challenging to select the most suitable artists, for a particular curated show, and situate them in the proper context and promote them in order to bring in fresh ideas and works in the art world. The art world generally is comfortable with the well-known and saleable names. Therefore, to justify the new and unknown artists and make their works saleable is a tough call. However, once the selection is done and the show is conceptualized well, then the promotional talk shows, pre-opening press release and a firm conviction leads me to overcome the challenge.', 'My curatorial projects have, I believe, are creating a visible impact on the art community and also on the society. Because I have done some successful art exhibitions showcasing the young and upcoming artists and because the art viewing public has shown great interest in such shows, the younger generation of artists are feeling enthused and encouraged to continue their engagement with their art practice with a renewed energy and hope. The general awareness thus created that art is also a living practice and not just a heritage phenomenon, is surely reassuring for me.', 'Curating Show at ATI (Government) center Kolkata, the show is on Traditional and Modern Art in Bengal. \r\nCurating Show at Ganges Art, Kolkata with three female artists.\r\nCollaborating different academic projects with Accademia Albertina Torino, Turin and University of Valladolid in collaboration with Casa de la India, Spain.', 'I would like to see my dream comes alive one day. One such dream is to build an art space where young creative personnel will come, stay and work and they will be able to sustain themselves from this space.', '[{"download_link":"files/UOizgQJBvDDX3su2K0zEMBGQhGyGivIRY8PfvdU3.jpg","original_name":"Self.jpg"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/pHw94T7t1splywmBonm8YqSjxtv2dQs9NDpcJIgA.jpg","original_name":"CERTIFICATE, Charukala, Dhaka, Bangladesh.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/h0iZOt7P0jQeTn7HxHec3qEqvYIZP01OIRLBCJCP.pdf","original_name":"My Curatorial Projects in different Galleries and Museum.pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/1TUga1uvy6e5uJaijBGwftXXC70oH8MPTmsq3aYi.jpg","original_name":"Recommendation Letter for Soma Pg 2 0f 2.jpg"}]', '2021-11-15 10:08:26', '2021-11-15 10:08:26', NULL, 0),
	(47, 7, 'Y', 'Performing Arts (Music, Dance & Theatre)', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Shashwati Garai Ghosh', '1980-10-11', '9831734178', 'shashwatigg@gmail.com', '3 Charunagar, Brahmapur, Kolkata - 700096', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/shashwatigg', 'https://www.facebook.com/shashwati.garaighosh', 'https://www.instagram.com/shashwatigarai', 'https://www.facebook.com/Angashuddhi/', 'https://www.instagram.com/angashuddhi/', 'Hailing from a family of artists I grew to believe that art reflects life. As a child I was curious and creative, enjoyed movements and liked to be engaged in artistic activities. Learning dance at a very tender age gave me immense happiness then and later paved the way for a career in it.\r\n\r\nI always knew that I wanted to live with an art form. I also knew that I would do whatever it takes to train myself to become an independent artist with an individualistic approach to my chosen art form.  \r\n\r\nThat desire started taking shape when I joined my guru Sharmila Biswas years ago.\r\n\r\nI was intrigued by her approach towards Odishi and the vast body of work. I took things very slowly to understand every bit of the training, the research, the intricacies, and the volume of the process. \r\n\r\nMy dance career just flowed through these processes. And what I most enjoyed is the freedom within the hardcore professional life of an artiste.\r\n\r\nA very early start to my solo career gave me the necessary experience and confidence to start my own dance institute. My Institute ‘Angashuddhi – Home for Odishi’ is an initiative to nurture, and pass on the experience of learning Odishi dance to the next generation. I strive to encourage the appreciation of the Odishi dance form and imbibe its roots to dancers and art enthusiasts alike. \r\n\r\nI am very content as a dancer, and Odishi is my language of expression. I express my ideas, thoughts and creativity as a soloist, a choreographer, and a teacher.\r\n\r\nChallenges and hurdles exist. But they are part of an exciting journey.', 'Angashuddhi – Home for Odishi', 'Institute founder, soloist, choreographer, teacher', '22', '2021-06-30', '3 Charunagar, Brahmapur', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700096', '9831734178', 'shashwatigg@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'I have always been impressed, influenced, and intrigued by my guru Sharmila Biswas\' vast body of work. From her I learnt the importance of methodical research, and a deliberate approach to creating original work.\r\n\r\nI was privileged to receive special training from dance stalwarts like Guru Kelucharan Mohapatra, Smt. Kalanidhi Narayanan, Smt. Sonal Mansingh, Smt. Malavika Sarukkai, and Guru Durgacharan Ranbir. That association was priceless, and I gained critical strength and confidence helping me every step of my professional career.\r\n\r\nMy training with fitness expert Dr. Kannan Pugazhendi completely changed my perspective towards staying fit as a dancer. That learning helped me create my own dance fitness regime that I\'ve incorporated in my training method.\r\n\r\nAchievements:\r\n1. First recipient of Guru Kelucharan Mohapatra Yuva Pratibha Samman\r\n2. Ustad Bismillah Khan Yuva Puraskar\r\n3. Kalavahini Senior Fellowship\r\n4. Sanskriti Madhobi Chatterjee Memorial Fellowship\r\n5. National Scholarship, Ministry of Culture, Government of India.', 'Managing my solo career while also running my own dance institute, has been an ongoing challenge. I learn and overcome many hurdles everyday… It is a constant process.', 'As a performer and teacher of a classical dance form I believe I bear the responsibility of preserving and passing on a very rich cultural artefact. With my life\'s work I have strived to achieve that. In the process, I hope to leave my own footprints of artistic thoughts and ideas in the sand of time.', 'I would like to continue to create original work as a choreographer, and contribute further to my pedagogical repertoire.', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/S1Ck5htowNnmJBlGMrHxfX7nBiOVwEXpdY6eAmjw.jpg","original_name":"Sgg.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/RtEiL7escOV8p5WhR7NFp6ZklejS7NJkKiTz2L49.mp4","original_name":"sgg video clip.mp4"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/5PCmcGFz2MDimq4SQaStrcG7RUME5Y3fqPHIN6C4.jpg","original_name":"Bismillah Khan Award.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/0xKQ6AGzQhCgXG1j3adqRke4TpczmCh1iXEp94n0.jpg","original_name":"Review.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/8ojpCMQIuoIMsEvo2yjsROYMF36trSFfxzTTq8gX.jpg","original_name":"Sgg.jpeg"}]', '2021-11-15 11:27:12', '2021-11-15 11:27:12', NULL, 0),
	(48, 1, 'N', 'Academia & Education', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Dr Sharmistha Chatterjee', '1981-01-13', '9830008702', 'sharmi.archaeology@gmail.com', '153/3J, APC Road, Kolkata: 700006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Dr Sharmistha Chatterjee, archaeologist by profession, has obtained PhD and Gold medal from the Department of Archaeology, University of Calcutta (2012). Her Post-Doctoral research (2015) is from the Indian Council of Historical Research (ICHR, New Delhi). She has been awarded with International Fellowships like CWIT and Nehru Trust to work in the British Museum, Victoria Albert Museum, London, and Ashmolean in Oxford. She has participated in International Projects with fundings from UKIERI, ERCP, British Academy and UGC (National). She has conducted classes through NGOs for the street children of south Kolkata. She has worked at the grass root level by engaging communities and practicing Cultural Resource Management (CRM) in the rural areas of Bankura and Bishnupur. Her research has covered entire stretches of the riverine valleys of the western uplands of Bengal in the districts of Bankura, Bardhaman and Medinipur. She has discovered 64 archaeological sites in the vicinity of the medieval temple town of Bishnupur (Bankura, West Bengal). She has been engaged with the rural communities for imparting educating reaching out to the people for welfare activities. Her work on the Bishnupur temples and the region is published in the leading National and International Journals. Her interests are field and cultural studies, women empowerment, and education reforms. Dr Chatterjee is Assistant Professor in the Institute of Social Sciences, Amity University, Kolkata.', 'Amity University', 'Faculty', '15', '2021-06-30', 'Newtown KOlkata', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700135', '9830008702', 'schatterjee5@kol.amity.edu', 'https://www.amity.edu/kolkata/', NULL, 'I have contributed archaeological studies which has been always a patriarchal domain. From conducting field work in most inaccessible areas to working with the communities which are under abject poverty, my academic career has not only helped me in developing my knowledge skills but also shaped me as a true human. I have contributed on International platforms by presenting case studies from eastern India (Bihar, Orissa and Bengal) and also published my in recognized journals. I have participated in International Projects with Universities, both in India and abroad. I have also bagged International Fellowships from the Queens University, Belfast, Nehru Trust and CWIT, UK. I have developed communication with the rural communities through the CRM practices which have helped them in knowing about education and heritage of India.', 'Biggest challenge was working in the most inhospitable areas of Bihar and the western uplands of Bengal. I have been stuck in areas with dense forests, remote villages for hours without food and communication. This was a part of my PhD field project and I could only overcome this through the presence of mind, perseverance and above all through God\'s grace. Having lost my mother at a tender age was equally difficult. She left me when I needed her the most. But I believe she has been there to guide me throughout and realize my dreams and aspirations.', 'I have connected with both top-down and bottom-up approaches and tried to impart education on cultural heritage and awareness amongst the rural people of Bengal and Bihar. I have communicated with the local masses wherefrom I have learnt their problems, their approaches and these have been published in the international and national journals. These have been put forward to the policy makers and the concerned authorities for both poverty alleviation and creating awareness for heritage conservation and participation.', 'I am planning to work particularly for the women in the rural domains and in this regard have planned to pen down their problems in the form of a book titled as " landscape and Gender: Evaluating gender roles and genderscapes in eastern India". Work with the marginalized sections , particularly women should start from the ground level and I am trying my level best to be one of the facilitators in bringing women to where they belong.', 'I would like to \'Thank\' and express my gratitude to platforms like Sanmarg Aparajita which has allowed women like us to share their views and in the long run this is surely allowing women of every section to emerge from darkness and marginalization towards the indispensable and ineffable light of glory and vigor.', '[{"download_link":"files/6Jnx08sPvff4ym77mZJwhVL1BQCKguJilspd8co9.jpg","original_name":"Sharmistha Chatterjee.jpg"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/PkseGcs5xv2QzK8kCnsPEyZBnQLt4ZXGua1yYXaS.pdf","original_name":"Documents.pdf"}]', NULL, NULL, '2021-11-15 14:50:40', '2021-11-15 14:50:40', NULL, 0),
	(49, 1, 'N', 'Academia & Education', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Bratati Bhattacharyya', '1965-08-25', '9874993188', 'bratatibhatt25@gmail.com', 'Av House ,107 Southern Avenue,  Kolkata - 700029', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/bratati-bhattacharyya-b  0281631', 'https://www.facebook.com/bratati.bhattacharyya.7', 'https://www.instagram.com/bhattacharyyabratati/', 'https://www.facebook.com/CBSKolkata/', 'https://www.instagram.com/calcuttabusinessschool/?hl=en', 'I am a passionate Entrepreneur, Educationist and a lifelong learner. I completed my Higher Secondary in 1984, graduated in Economics in 1987 thereafter did a masters in Economics from the University of Bombay in 1989 and a Post-graduation in Financial Management from IGNOU. Governor’s Gold Medalist from Jadavpur University for my B. Ed and recipient of a Merit scholarship from the University of Bombay. Have 30 years of working experience. At present pursuing Doctoral studies at the University of Liverpool.  After  7 years in investment banking, I joined the Education world. From a high school teacher to Vice Principal at Ashok hall, former Principal of G.D. Birla Centre for Education and former Chief Education Officer of Techno India Group, founder Director/promoter of a preprimary school and currently Secretary-General and Chief Executive Officer of an educational institution, Shikshayatan Foundation. It manages, Marwari Balika Vidyalaya, Shri Shikshayatan School, Shri Shikshayatan College and Calcutta Business School. I am on the board of different Educational Societies and schools, Co-Chairman of the Education Committee of CII ER and a member of the Education Committee of BCC&I. Recognition: Was awarded as the "Indian Iconic Educationist" (For Best Education System & Services in West Bengal) from the Indo Socio Development Association, "Inspiring Best Teacher” from the University Of Engineering & Management" of Kolkata & Jaipur and “Bharat Vidya Shiromani” from the International Institute of Education & Management, Excellence in Managing Educational Institution from LASWEB, “Women of Worth” from The Sister Nivedita University, “Exceptional Women of Excellence” from Women’s Indian Chamber of Commerce & Industry (WICCI), "Changemaker" from Aditya Birla Academy.“Radha Krishnan Institutional Award Excellence 2021”- Shikshayatan Foundation was handed over for the outstanding contribution towards Higher Education. A speaker and panellist for workshops and seminars. Does capacity building for faculties. Is a passionate social worker. Writes articles.', 'Shikshayatan Foundation', 'Overall  Head of the Organisation Shikshayatan Foundation. Oversees all the  four units . Is also part of the governing body of all the 4 units.', '30', '2021-06-30', '11 lord Sinha  Road,', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700029', '9874993188', 'bratatibhatt25@gmail.com', 'https://shikshayatanfoundation.org', NULL, 'My key learning has been loving whatever I do and doing whatever I love. The word "I" was replaced by us. Learnt the power of relationships and teamwork. Time management, accepting change and working towards opportunities amidst different challenges. As an Investment banker, my learning was understanding the brand value and retaining trust in the market. As a high school teacher solving students’ issues having learning difficulties. Shouldered and learned administrative work that included students\' discipline, preparing timetables and organizing substitution duties over and above normal teaching. As the Vice-principal worked towards the strength thereby maximizing the potentials of faculties and students through a thorough analysis of data. Despite several obstacles, it was ensured that students learnt. As a principal, the focus broadened to academic excellence. Learning management systems were developed way back in 2006 and also the concept of no bags till class five was introduced. Special worksheets were designed for students to reduce homework.  Three shifts started to accommodate students to be part of the prestigious school. 2007 the ISC topper was from the school.  Learnt about multiple intelligence and its benefit in children\'s learning from the pre-primary stage. As the Chief Education Officer of multiple schools, the learning was multifaceted, standardizing the curriculum and assessment pattern, developing human resources, opening new schools, working towards affiliation of schools and improving quality of education. As a Secretary-General, the learning was on empowering human lives, developing the community, working towards a green environment. Learnt to deal with a different spectrum of faculties from pre-primary level to post-graduate faculties and students. Learnt to create leaders for the organization and transformation of resources making the institute a learning environment by bringing out the best through regular feedback. Overcoming challenges, finding opportunities and welcoming change through collaboration, connection, critical thinking and creativity.', 'There have been multiple challenges in my career and have taken them as an opportunity. I came from a corporate sector and then joined the school. I had to do my B.Ed along with students who were much younger than me in age. With two small children, I managed my classes, never took leave even on my exams day and yet I got the first position from Jadavpur University. This was possible because of the mental support I received from management peers, colleagues and family members. As a VP, I ensured that students never missed a class during the preparation of a program called Spectrum by making a new timetable to accommodate practice time. This was possible as I trusted my strength and believed in teamwork. As the Chief education officer, all schools were brought under the same umbrella in accepting the same question paper for all subjects. Teamwork has helped and acceptance of change was embraced. As a secretary-general one of the biggest challenges in making the institute 100% digital. Several ways were adopted to convince faculty, students and parents in 2015. The latest challenge was ensuring that students never missed a single class during the lockdown. This was possible and we started with classes on 23rd March 2020. We all took the change as an opportunity and the team all worked together towards achieving the goal. Any challenge that I have faced I have worked towards being assertive and the power of relationships. Self-control, Patience and Perseverance have helped me to overcome these difficult moments and to find inspiration and push through. Every answer I believe lies with oneself. Every challenge starts with oneself and it ends with oneself. Others have been a motivation and I have been an inspiration to balance out the most difficult times.', 'My involvement in the day to day work from grass root level has helped people to transform and bring changes to themselves. With the digitalized organization, parents/ faculty and students have all been upgraded fully. There are different projects of community services where midday meals are provided for students. Organized fundraising for a Sundarbans School as an advisor. Helped old age homes and work voluntarily for organizations like Legal Aid Services where people are trained to do counselling and be aware of legal rights helping old people and vulnerable society. Have organized classrooms with tribal children at Falta. We are involved with different rural immersion projects for empowering women. Moreover, I have organized and have engaged myself in skill development & capacity development for people. I have been working towards improving women’s education from the standpoints of both community organizing and technology education to empower people in the capacity of a speaker and a panellist for several Workshops, Seminars and Webinars. I have written and published several articles on education. I enjoy coaching school / higher education educators and I believe in globalization and a borderless education. At present, I am working towards higher education classroom teaching and also to work towards woman leadership. As the education committee co-chairman of CII, we organize several programs for students and faculty to have an impact on society. Many activities have been added to our curriculum that has empowered our students like sports, performing arts, playing chess, making movies, and learning entrepreneurship programs. Have done television shows to reach out to people.  Facilitated working towards students with special needs. Working on strengths of people.  I have impacted many lives and many who have been my students and other staff members from time to time over so many years.', 'Future plans are there for making a skill development centre, introducing sports management course and a leadership training cell for school heads in Eastern India through our own management school. Moreover, working towards developing and opening a school with sports and performing arts as the main core subject while teaching concepts. Working towards opening a University which would help to reach out to many students at different levels. Making the maximum out of technology where learning can happen everywhere and from anywhere. Apart from that, my next priority would be to motivate and educate people through experiential learning and develop hands-on skills, which would help one be employable to be economically independent. Further, I would like to work towards preservation and self-sustainability, to make people aware of health, the environment and ways to protect the same. As a woman, it is not only important to educate girls but also boys in the right spirit. My next mission is also to work towards women leadership and transformation Working out to reach out to students remotely to empower them physically and digitally. Working towards the nation development, making people know and learn one’s own responsibility towards sustainable development focusing largely on health education, school education, technical education and management education. Enable one to represent one’s interest in a responsible way to bring about a transformation from within oneself and also in others by being economically independent, politically stable leading to a social transformation. Further, I like to work towards and encourage women leadership in every sphere. The planning is all part of the journey and many people would be involved along with me to reach out to my goals.  Will promote research work among students and faculties to find newer pedagogies for learning.', 'I do have a lot of aspirations for the future.   My personal achievements are that I love my work, I love to solve complex problems, I like to help people to find a solution to sustain themselves.   I dream of a  country whose people will be educated through mapping with different sectors and I also believe in first working closely with people who are in and around me and enable one to represent one’s interest in a responsible way to bring about a transformation within oneself and also in others by being economically independent, politically stable leading to a social transformation. Trust comes from the power of relationships and values every relationship. People around you are the greatest trust. Moreover, in the course of my life my friends, relatives colleagues have all helped me to fulfil many of my dreams in some form or the other.  \r\nCredibility, respect and fairness have been my biggest strength. I am grateful to people who have been sensitive, responsible and dependable in building my confidence. People, who have critically analyzed me has further allowed me to see things from a different perspective which has built my resilience. Every drop has helped me to resonate and I have learned to empathize with people in balancing official work and personal life. Team building, being connected and collaboration has helped me to have the self-confidence to ensure that words match actions\r\n  I look forward to taking up different responsibilities in future that would be a support for reaching out to maximum students where learning would be simplified and the fear for mathematics and history would be reduced making learning fun and being lifelong learners.', '[{"download_link":"files/BRJJ9l12ugfyMeLBEUfxNMXPcpPKrgIELrvoJGEW.jpg","original_name":"IMG_20180717_003605.JPG"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/h2A3c1qMBknAyJ4bClPniv2DuO5g3bkASxy4BxIT.pdf","original_name":"SG-certificates.pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/wEzokfiri1xLDUe0ctOqQb2I6zVdSuGLU8Y4LyOv.pdf","original_name":"07 CR MA CERTI.pdf"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/XJKQzzBCN43Q6Sgut0x9b822ZdNlGaeyIdx8QHQp.jpg","original_name":"certificate image.jpg"}]', '2021-11-15 22:25:57', '2021-11-15 22:25:57', NULL, 0),
	(50, 6, 'N', 'Creative Arts (Art & Photography)', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neelanjana Ghose', '1955-06-29', '9830471516', 'neelanjanaghose@yahoo.co.in', 'Block 5, Flat 50; 28/1A, Gariahat Road. Kolkata 700029', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/KanthaByNeelanjanaGhose', 'kanthabyneelanjana', 'https://www.facebook.com/KanthaByNeelanjanaGhose', 'kanthabyneelanjana', 'I started my journey as a costume designer in 1978 and gone on to work the craft of kantha since the last 35 years. Born and raised in Santiniketan in the midst of art and culture, I have been always consumed by it and have developed a special interest in textiles. My mother, Sreelata Sarkar, being one of the pioneers of the kantha revival, I followed her footsteps and have tried to carry on her legacy after her. My endeavour has been to bringing in modernity and contemporary aesthetics to the incredible tradition of the kantha craft, to make it sustainable and for its heritage to be preserved. I have been working tireless in supporting the 150 women artisans who work with me and create an environment where young women will come forward and learn the craft and keep it alive. I\'ve also started an NGO called Guri Run, through which we train women in rural West Bengal in the craft, hence providing an avenue of livelihood and preserving the craft. I have held exhibitions of my work in various places in India and also in Rome, Sweden and Dhaka. I have also written a book in Bangla on the craft of kantha.', 'Neelanjana Ghose', 'o	Neelanjana has been working with the kantha craft for over three decades.  She started in the early 80s, assisting her mother – the pioneer of kantha revival – Sreelata Sarkar, and has since dedicated her life in carrying forward this legacy. Neelanjana has weaved in her eclectic sensibilities in the traditional art form and has significantly contributed to making its appeal more global.  Neelanjana is also a well know costume designers and have worked in over 20 feature films including those of Goutam Ghose (all his features), Bedabrata Pain (Chittagong), Suman Ghosh (Podokkhep), Anjan Das (Shanjbatir Roopkathara) o	She has held several exhibitions of her kantha creations in Kolkata, Dhaka, Hyderabad, Bombay, Delhi, Rome. o	Showcased her collection in Göteberg, Sweden with Wendell Rodricks and Rahul Mishra in 2010.  o	Conceptualised and designed a show on the Mahabharata in 2011 o	Associated with the Bishwa Bangla - West Bengal Govt. initiated Brand from 2016.', '35', '2021-06-30', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '9830471516', 'neelanjanaghose@yahoo.co.in', NULL, NULL, 'Although I was a student of literature the creativity and sense of local rural people always attracted me. I learnt the art of designs since my childhood from my mother Smt Sreelata Sarkar. My mother was a connoisseur of Kantha embroidery and she took active initiative for its revival. I was inspired by her and tried to improvise and experiment with a global vision. I am happy that my humble work has been appreciated by the art and craft lovers. I also started working in cinema with my husband Goutam Ghose since the late seventies. I became the costume designer for his first feature film in Telugu \'Maa Bhoomi\' because there was none to look after the costumes!\r\nSince then costume designing has become my other passion and profession as well. Many of the films have won National and International awards. I believe still there\'s "miles to go" and many more things to achieve.', 'Creating every work of art is a challenge. Whether it is a small piece of Kantha or a large one. Just like in cinema a small film or a big film production. I try to do each and every assignment with utmost sincerity , passion and joy.\r\nWhen I Visualize or conceptualise a Kantha work perhaps many elements of our incredible art heritage and global traditions work together in my subconsciousness. Art moves in an unending way.', 'With my kantha initiatives I always try to help and support financially the women who are economically challenged in our society.\r\nIn my cinematic ventures I always try to be associated with artistic and socially relevant films', 'It has become difficult to plan anything specifically with kantha in this difficult time. Trying to experiment with different kinds of products and wishing that a time will come soon when we can start working as we are used to.\r\nAt present I am working in a film, an Indo Italian International co- production', 'Life and art have become even more challenging in this trying time of pandemic. I hope "We shall overcome ".', '[{"download_link":"files/4U3HknZDWMMpGBMP9Y8OCS4NfNG4f06S5X6b2Rme.png","original_name":"khuku.png"}]', NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/EtnxjM4hyFRIWbXemDYaw0nAY7tUrndUebBuhAgw.jpg","original_name":"dsc01825.JPG"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/XyPhXyw3o26ncahMC3B5bONxMtHduyqOns4U6AC1.pdf","original_name":"Neelanjana Ghose Bio \'21.pdf"}]', '2021-11-16 12:31:10', '2021-11-16 12:31:10', NULL, 0),
	(51, 1, 'N', 'Academia & Education', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Kavneet Khullar', '1963-04-02', '9830115422', 'khullar.noni@gmail.com', '8, Ho Chi Minh Sarani, Harrington Mansions. Flat No.20. 4th Floor', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/akshar.school1998/', NULL, '“The world would alas be so much duller, if we were all one colour!”\r\n\r\nKavneet Khullar started her career at the Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy and moved on to join Ms Neena Singh, Founder of Divyayan Montessori School, to make it the first Inclusive Montessori. Recognising the need for inclusion of children with Additional Needs in a mainstream school, Akshar the first Inclusive, I.S.C School in Kolkata was established in 1998.  She is the Trustee and the Principal of Akshar, who believes that it is the right of children with Disabilities to study alongside Mainstream Children; not a privilege. \r\n\r\nAkshar is a diverse blend of young minds with a common goal to  achieve excellence through compassion and care. It grew out of the necessity to build a school constantly searching for alternatives to the traditional system. She sees every child as unique and if given the right opportunity, they can be nurtured to achieve their fullest potential. \r\n\r\nShe has presented papers on “Inclusion” and “Building a Relationship of Mutuality” in several forums, stressing the need for ‘Education for All’, addressing Principals, Teachers, Parents and Children. She hopes to open a Life Skills Training Centre for adults with disabilities, equipping them with the necessary skills for employment.\r\n\r\nShe is a Member of the Governing Body and School Managing Committee of the Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy. She is a member of the Internal Quality Assurance Cell (IQAC), Loreto College in the field of Education.\r\n\r\nShe is the Trustee and Founder of The Harrington Street Arts Centre, a platform for adults and children alike to showcase their creativity. When it comes to the protection of  the environment, in her own small way, she chooses to contribute to the global environmental movement by adopting simple and sustainable changes to her daily living.', 'Akshar', 'Trustee & Principal', '33', '2021-06-30', '35 Diamond Harbour Road, Kolkata 700027', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700027', '9681200418', 'kavneet@aksharschool.org', 'www.aksharschool.org', NULL, 'Key Learnings - \r\n• Acquiring knowledge, not just knowing. Education is unlocking a world of potential\r\n• Teaching should be relevant, authentic and valuable to each child\r\n• Keeping abreast with the developing world and therefore equipping each child with those skills which will help them in the near future\r\n• To be part of the solution, not add to the problem\r\n• Learning to deal with failure as much as success\r\n\r\n\r\nKey Achievements - \r\n• Akshar being a pioneer in the field of inclusion and also being a successful inclusive model\r\n• The Telegraph School Awards, for the School that Dares\r\n• The Telegraph School Awards, for The School of the Year, 2018\r\n• THE EARLY CHILDHOOD ASSOCIATION AWARD - 2018\r\n• PATTON AWARD FOR ‘A SCHOOL THAT CARES’ - 2009  \r\nPresented by The Telegraph School Awards for Excellence\r\n• BRITISH COUNCIL INTERNATIONAL SCHOOL AWARD - 2009\r\n• ADAMAS INTERNATIONAL SCHOOL AWARD FOR \'A SCHOOL THAT LOOKS \r\nBEYOND – 2005 \r\nPresented by The Telegraph School Awards for Excellence', 'When Akshar was started, the challenge was whether parents of mainstream students would admit their child into an inclusive school and merge the so far “divorced” worlds of the special and mainstream children. This, however, did not daunt us. I knew that we at Akshar were doing the correct thing. I knew that the recipients of the benefit of an inclusive school would not only be confined to those children with special needs, but also for mainstream children. Children would learn from the lesser-abled, and observe how they strive to achieve their goals despite limitations. They would grow up to be sensitive young children with sound humane values. \r\n\r\nThe challenge for Akshar at the outset was getting parents of the Mainstream children to admit their child. Some questioned the concept and wondered whether their child\'s education would be compromised. We started with a total of 70 children till class II. Today we are a full grown I.S.C school with cent percent achievers. \r\n\r\nThe victory today is that a lot more parents of mainstream children would like to admit their children to Akshar because of the values inculcated in their children in an inclusive environment. Akshar conducts workshops on Inclusion and Education for All, at the outset of every academic year, for parents. \r\n\r\nWe must praise our teachers. It is their sheer motivation to learn more that keeps them closely affiliated with Akshar and its success. Workshops like Quality Circle Time conducted by Jenny Mosley, Global Trends and Best Practices in Education by Scholastic India, Workshop on Theatre Education in School conducted by The American Centre, Dyslexia - D.A.R.E to Win, a conference organised by Breaking through Dyslexia, to name a few, have worked extremely well in skill upgradation for our teachers.', 'The first step towards bringing about significant change in society is by building awareness. This can only be done by leading by example. Akshar, by virtue of being a pioneer in the field of Inclusive Education, has caused parents and students alike to accept, include and be sensitive to those that are differently-abled. At the outset, it not only ignited a dialogue, but the model in itself was a living representation of the movement.', '• Developing a Life Skills Unit for identifying skills in young adults with additional needs and help facilitate employment\r\n\r\n• To make Akshar an environmentally conscious and sustainable hub with an aim to minimise waste. The idea of switching to sustainability and finding alternatives is a prerequisite in the current times and it is a necessity for us to drive this sense of environmental responsibilities in students, parents, teachers and staff members. Our mantra at Akshar is to "Reimagine. Recreate. Restore."\r\n\r\nTo make Akshar truly follow Rudolf Steiner theory that a students moral, spiritual and creative sides need as much attention as their intellect. Each student that steps out of Akshar must stand apart to take on the world embodying the facets of a holistic human being. Happy and confident in his own skin!', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/dtPqLjpyllfjgGH5UCm2Z4iMOvtC49TIDwihFsW3.jpg","original_name":"Kavneet Khullar.jpeg"}]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-11-16 20:53:55', '2021-11-16 20:53:55', NULL, 0),
	(52, 4, 'Y', 'Csr & Social Service', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sarbani Das Roy', '1965-01-16', '9330889568', 'sarbani@isankalpa.org', '19/3 PITAMBAR GHATAK LANE, Kolkata 700027', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BmWd5dHtxgk&t=17s', 'https://www.facebook.com/sarbani.d.roy/', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/iswarsankalpa', 'iswarsankalpango', 'https://www.socialworkindia.in/profiles/sharbani-das-roy\r\n\r\nSarbani Das Roy - Co Founder and Director of Iswar Sankalpa is an Ashoka Fellow and a social development crusader. She has Pioneered an alternative pathway of care for the homeless persons with mental illness which has been recognized by World Health Organization as one of the 5 best practices in community outreach program in the world. The main foci of her work has been • To restore the dignity and autonomy of persons with psychosocial disability.  • To develop a care module that brings about overall wellness through the healing power of self-reliance and community support • Developing Process Sensitivity and Organisation Transformation, Developing linkages for growth and sustainability • Personal Growth, Self Renewal, Leadership and Individual Coaching, , Conflict Resolution, Changemaker.  She has also initiated an integrated approach to health care by making available mental health care at municipality primary health care centers, for the urban home-based poor in Kolkata. She was instrumental in opening the first shelter for homeless women with psychosocial disability in collaboration with Kolkata Municipal Corporation. 3000 homeless persons with mental heath conditions have been touched by Iswar Sankalpa and more than 550 women have recovered from the shelter. Iswar Sankalpa\'s Sarbari womens’ shelter programme has received HUDCO Award for Best Practices to \'Improve the Living Environment 2014-15\' under ‘Training & Health Services for Urban Poor’ Category . Iswar Sankalpa is the first Kolkata based NGO to receive such an award. She has encouraged women with mental health conditions to become economically independent by getting trained in the confectionary unit – ‘ Crust & Core’, the vocational training unit – Saksham and the cultivation and sale of vegetables in the various projects – “ Nayagram”. All of this is supported by guidance in functional literacy without which empowerment is not completed. Recognition: Recipient of 2019 ‘ Outstanding Individual Working for Cause of Persons with Disability ‘ from Government of West Bengal.\r\nCertificate of Recognition from the West Bengal State Government for contribution towards protection of women’s right, 2016\r\nCertificate of recognition as the ‘CHANGEMAKER TO SOCIETY’ by the Hon’ble Governor of West Bengal Shri Keshari Nath Tripathi, 2015', 'ISWAR SANKALPA', 'DIRECTOR', '20', '2021-06-30', '19/3 PITAMBAR GHATAK LANE', 'KOLKATA', 'West Bengal', '700027', '9330889568', 'sarbani@isankalpa.org', 'www.isankalpa.org', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BmWd5dHtxgk&t=17s', 'Successfully demonstrated that one can develop treatment, care and reintegration strategies for homeless persons with psychosocial disability, using the community care approach.\r\n\r\n	Designed and implemented the first program for the homeless with psychosocial disability in the city of Kolkata.\r\n	Developed a unique community based module of care that offers a whole spectrum of healthcare and psychosocial services ranging from services on the streets and at shelters to rehabilitation, reintegration into society, while also ensuring a continuum of care.\r\n	Developed an assisted community living for recovering homeless women with mental illness in the village of Kashipur, Bhangore, 24 Pgs – which offers agriculture and animal husbandry as livelihood options and enables 15 women to live in a commune with increasing independence. \r\n	Developed a skill development program for 15 homeless women with mental illness in confectionary industry. This has led to the successful launch of a café – ‘Crust & Core”.\r\n	Spearheaded partnership building processes with the government agencies, police and nongovernment agencies.\r\n	Spearheaded the advocacy and awareness building campaign for the cause. \r\n	Created community-friendly, holistic solution for effective mental healthcare delivery to urban home-based poor population by integrating mental health clinics with Municipality ward based primary health centres.', 'Just ten months after I started the organization Iswar Sankalpa, our Co Founder Dr K.L Narayanan had a sudden heart attack and he passed away. At that time I was left completely broken - financially, emotionally and also totally lost in the pursuit of how to manage this wholly unknown social problem - the homeless person with severe mental illness. At that time the organization was new and had no resources to contemplate an institutional model also. At that point I had only two paths ahead of me. I could close the organization which was only 10 month old and pursue my professional career in corporate sector. Or I could plunge into the problem and find my way despite all the challenges. I decided to take the latter path. The rest is history.', '• Iswar Sankalpa has been working towards the protection of the rights of persons with psychosocial disabilities (primarily the homeless and slum-based population) since 2007– upholding their right to health services, right to comprehensive habilitation/rehabilitation, their right to employment, their right to safe housing and their right to access government facilities, entitlements and other benefits, by setting up a continuum of multi-pronged care and support. It has been striving to build a model of inclusive care for the most vulnerable and least legally protected population by designing and redesigning programmes and strategies based on their emerging needs. A combination of services (outreach, shelter, day care centre, clinic-based, community centred…) and reintegration support programmes (skills training, non-formal education, access to entitlements, community living, income generation programmes, selfadvocacy…) have been developed over the years since no one size fits all and no particular solution is the only solution to the complexities and the magnitude of the problem in hand. The work being rooted in the Community Based Rehabilitation (CBR) model is addressing 5 major aspects of living: Health, Education, Livelihood, Social and Empowerment. With the target group’s choice, agency and participation forming the nucleus of the work, the model underlines the importance of multi-sectoral collaboration (family of the primary stakeholders, law enforcement agency, government, medical body, community, civil society and media) for facilitating sustainable community reintegration of the vulnerable social groups. \r\n•	3440 homeless persons with psychosocial disability, living on the streets, have been provided treatment & services through community based care model\r\n•	604 women have been provided a safe shelter.\r\n•	129 men have been provided a safe shelter.\r\n•	468 persons have been restored to home across India\r\n•	775 persons with psychosocial disability are in employment\r\n•	716 persons have been provided vocational training\r\n•	120 persons have received ration card, 176 persons have received disability card, 264 persons have received adhar card and 171 persons have their own bank account.\r\n•	4633  persons from low income group families have been provided treatment, counseling & CBR support through Urban Mental Health Clinics\r\n•	895 awareness campaigns were conducted in the community for sensitization and education covering more than 51935 people\r\n•	288 health workers, medical officers and police personnel have been provided mental health training\r\n•	A network of 476 CBOs has been created to provide various support\r\n•	2 mental health committees have been formed involving local councillors, community leaders and community members', 'I would like to work to offer opportunities for our men/ women to be financially independent. I hope to have small kiosks/ shops in parts of the city where products made by persons with psychosocial disability are bought, used and recommended for their worth and not for sympathy. I want to see every person have a purpose in life.', 'https://www.telegraphindia.com/west-bengal/calcutta/who-recognition-for-city-ngo-which-helps-the-homeless/cid/1819321', '[{"download_link":"files/D77KwXClrshc114Dsj4RrKDBMGs9rshQT4Fxqzz0.jpg","original_name":"40 (2).JPG"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/G4k2mMR3Etfk5LXjqz1EnzvWoMPMU4D5DL6Wv60M.mp4","original_name":"Ashoka Video.mp4"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/0wPFJBb2cSX8wKn80sv0Q60fAv0Up4o4AG8bNQZQ.jpg","original_name":"State Award 3-12-19.jpeg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/KD09FfgrGJeg3NV5cQFHvwjUyhO6dGU4OpKDmpdD.jpg","original_name":"dr kalam and me.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/doUi6nqXzlYeEhnUfdr4tkpw9AmFfjIY1utEQu42.pdf","original_name":"Iswar Sankalpa_Annual report_2019-20.pdf"}]', '2021-11-16 20:57:40', '2021-11-16 20:57:40', NULL, 0),
	(53, 6, 'Y', 'Creative Arts (Art & Photography)', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sangita Maity', '1989-04-29', '9433412820', 'sangitamaity123@gmail.com', 'Rabi Rashmi Abasan, Bungalow no. 16, Street no. 326, DJ-9 Newtown, Kolkata 700156. WB, India', NULL, NULL, 'maity.sangita', NULL, 'maity.sangita', 'Sangita Maity, born 1989 in Kanthi, West Bengal. \r\nLives and works in Kolkata. Sangita graduated and post-graduated in Print Making from Faculty of Visual Arts, Rabindra Bharati University in 2012 and 2014 respectively.\r\n \r\nSangita’s practice is focused on issues of labour, occupational migration and related socio-cultural and environmental issues that emerge during the extensive research that informs each of her projects. Following several years of engagement with the Barbil iron ore mines, one of India\'s largest of it’s kind located in the Keonjhar district of Orissa, she is now working with communities that revolve around rubber plantations in Tripura. She interacts with the land and its inhabitants to understand the region\'s ecology and politics.\r\n\r\nMaity has received Junior Fellowship from Ministry of Culture,2018 -2019 & CIMA Jury Award 2015. She has participated in Khoj Peers Residency 2014 at Khoj Artists Association in New Delhi.\r\n \r\nSangita has presented a solo show at Clark House Initiative, Mumbai in 2018. She was part of the show ‘ Look, Stranger! ’ Curated by Rahaab Allana for Serendipity Art Festival 2019. She has exhibited in Dr. Bhau Daji Lad Museum, Mumbai in 2016.', 'Freelance Visual Artist', 'Freelance Visual Artist', '7', '2021-06-30', 'Rabi Rashmi Abasan, Bungalow no. 16, Street no. 326, DJ-9 Newtown', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700156', '9433412820', 'sangitamaity123@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'Maity has received Junior Fellowship from Ministry of Culture,2018 -2019 & CIMA Jury Award 2015. She has participated in Khoj Peers Residency 2014 at Khoj Artists Association in New Delhi.\r\n \r\nSangita has presented a solo show at Clark House Initiative, Mumbai in 2018. She was part of the show ‘ Look, Stranger! ’ Curated by Rahaab Allana for Serendipity Art Festival 2019. She has exhibited in Dr. Bhau Daji Lad Museum, Mumbai in 2016.', 'Each day and each work is challenging for me. Overcoming or rather completing the work is part of the learning process to me. Moreover, such spontaneity only adds aesthetics in living.', 'Over the last few years, I have been working on marginalised people in the society, those who live far from the cities but has a distinct role in functioning the mega cities. In reality, they have been ignored in many ways. My work represents some of these situations into visual forms. These stories of living definitely reached to the viewers who otherwise might not be aware of these facts.', 'I am working on several projects coming up early next year. A solo exhibition in Delhi, another solo show at Art Basel Hong Kong in March where I will be presenting a body of work on the people living in Chotonagpur Plateau region in West Bengal, bordering areas of Jharkhand. Also, preparing a body of work for India Art Fair in February next year.', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/VfpyniZvAf3ipkDDkIvTiykCSYQsy4A9MwvoNHZj.jpg","original_name":"photo .jpg"}]', NULL, NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/shb5UoFuQLZlRjorfWmECjaMH2ouVrH2y913atOy.jpg","original_name":"work image1.jpg"}]', NULL, '2021-11-16 22:48:48', '2021-11-16 22:48:48', NULL, 0),
	(61, 3, 'N', 'Enterprise', 1, 'You Shine (5 to 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Anshu Agarwal', '1982-03-08', '9830085568', 'anshu.sbevents@gmail.com', '141 block G NEW Alipore, Lane opp gupta brothers', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/sbeventofficial/', 'www.instagram.com/sbevents.com', 'https://www.facebook.com/sbeventofficial/', 'www.instagram.com/sbevents_official', 'A small craft store named Scrap\'s N Bit\'s to satiate our crafty moods soon grew into a event decor company now known as SB Events.  The past 6 years of passion and effort into giving memorable experiences and detailing at small Do\'s and parties have helped us create a niche and a loyal clientele. A breakthrough moment was doing an event decor with Vogue India Atelier for renowned designer Tarun Tahiliani. In the new normal world again as people are celebrating Life again, SB Events has made a comeback with its vision of having \'Budget friendly yet detailed parties\'.', 'SB Events', 'Proprietor', '6', '2021-06-30', '141 Block G NEW Alipore,', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700053', '9830085568', 'anshu.sbevents@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'Key achievements : \r\nMall decor at Christmas for Quest Mall (2015)\r\nT2 Party Decor (2016) as a subsidiary vendor with TPP \r\nVogue India Atelier for Tarun Tahiliani (2019)', 'The biggest challenge is that as a Marwari daughter in law and mother from a well established business background, my work is not taken seriously by my Vendors and other people in the Event Industry. A successful entrepreneur one doesn\'t not leave a business opportunity but as a Mother i have dropped a few along the way, without comprising on my family time. This dissuades many co professionals and makes them question my passion and hard work. Having said that, at the same time I have established a clientele of similar minded people who appreciate my limitations and show 100 percent trust in my work, without taking their accounts to other people in the industry. This faith in my work is my biggest achievement that took a while to achieve.', 'As compared to current times, 10 years ago as a young mother, I found a huge gap in the industry, wherein we wanted Pinterest-like parties without making a huge dent in our pockets by going to top of the line event planners and decorators. That\'s when the idea took seed and we started events. Even after 6 years we can boast in the fact that you can get an instaworthy decor at a budget of your choice.', 'We plan to expand to a furniture rental and simple backdrop rental line not for other vendors but for clients to directly plan their parties without hiring an event planner.', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/iR6GPew8tmKx6eG4IOY4ND3Ixu8c9GXAw3vsYdMk.jpg","original_name":"IMG-20200727-WA0102.jpg"}]', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/pyaL53PCyzT1KaUa8mEjoswM3J8rZ8lXb0fAXNMd.jpg","original_name":"IMG_20211119_002511.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/BPIauSj5mRpqlIRG6KxWgf1r14aZBb09ZFsG0Lu6.jpg","original_name":"IMG_20211031_173540.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/TMV962SYMCGvlhPKJhzplGGRPnnxXzLK9NQ4Y1jp.jpg","original_name":"Screenshot_20211119_002609.jpg"}]', '2021-11-18 23:56:54', '2021-11-18 23:56:54', NULL, 0),
	(63, 4, 'Y', 'Csr & Social Service', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sarbani Das Roy (inserted)', '1965-01-16', '9330889568', 'sarbani@isankalpa.org', '19/3 PITAMBAR GHATAK LANE, Kolkata 700027', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BmWd5dHtxgk&t=17s', 'https://www.facebook.com/sarbani.d.roy/', NULL, 'https://www.facebook.com/iswarsankalpa', 'iswarsankalpango', 'https://www.socialworkindia.in/profiles/sharbani-das-roy\r\n\r\nSarbani Das Roy - Co Founder and Director of Iswar Sankalpa is an Ashoka Fellow and a social development crusader. She has Pioneered an alternative pathway of care for the homeless persons with mental illness which has been recognized by World Health Organization as one of the 5 best practices in community outreach program in the world. The main foci of her work has been • To restore the dignity and autonomy of persons with psychosocial disability.  • To develop a care module that brings about overall wellness through the healing power of self-reliance and community support • Developing Process Sensitivity and Organisation Transformation, Developing linkages for growth and sustainability • Personal Growth, Self Renewal, Leadership and Individual Coaching, , Conflict Resolution, Changemaker.  She has also initiated an integrated approach to health care by making available mental health care at municipality primary health care centers, for the urban home-based poor in Kolkata. She was instrumental in opening the first shelter for homeless women with psychosocial disability in collaboration with Kolkata Municipal Corporation. 3000 homeless persons with mental heath conditions have been touched by Iswar Sankalpa and more than 550 women have recovered from the shelter. Iswar Sankalpa\'s Sarbari womens’ shelter programme has received HUDCO Award for Best Practices to \'Improve the Living Environment 2014-15\' under ‘Training & Health Services for Urban Poor’ Category . Iswar Sankalpa is the first Kolkata based NGO to receive such an award. She has encouraged women with mental health conditions to become economically independent by getting trained in the confectionary unit – ‘ Crust & Core’, the vocational training unit – Saksham and the cultivation and sale of vegetables in the various projects – “ Nayagram”. All of this is supported by guidance in functional literacy without which empowerment is not completed. Recognition: Recipient of 2019 ‘ Outstanding Individual Working for Cause of Persons with Disability ‘ from Government of West Bengal.\r\nCertificate of Recognition from the West Bengal State Government for contribution towards protection of women’s right, 2016\r\nCertificate of recognition as the ‘CHANGEMAKER TO SOCIETY’ by the Hon’ble Governor of West Bengal Shri Keshari Nath Tripathi, 2015', 'ISWAR SANKALPA', 'DIRECTOR', '20', '2021-06-30', '19/3 PITAMBAR GHATAK LANE', 'KOLKATA', 'West Bengal', '700027', '9330889568', 'sarbani@isankalpa.org', 'www.isankalpa.org', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BmWd5dHtxgk&t=17s', 'Successfully demonstrated that one can develop treatment, care and reintegration strategies for homeless persons with psychosocial disability, using the community care approach.\r\n\r\n	Designed and implemented the first program for the homeless with psychosocial disability in the city of Kolkata.\r\n	Developed a unique community based module of care that offers a whole spectrum of healthcare and psychosocial services ranging from services on the streets and at shelters to rehabilitation, reintegration into society, while also ensuring a continuum of care.\r\n	Developed an assisted community living for recovering homeless women with mental illness in the village of Kashipur, Bhangore, 24 Pgs – which offers agriculture and animal husbandry as livelihood options and enables 15 women to live in a commune with increasing independence. \r\n	Developed a skill development program for 15 homeless women with mental illness in confectionary industry. This has led to the successful launch of a café – ‘Crust & Core”.\r\n	Spearheaded partnership building processes with the government agencies, police and nongovernment agencies.\r\n	Spearheaded the advocacy and awareness building campaign for the cause. \r\n	Created community-friendly, holistic solution for effective mental healthcare delivery to urban home-based poor population by integrating mental health clinics with Municipality ward based primary health centres.', 'Just ten months after I started the organization Iswar Sankalpa, our Co Founder Dr K.L Narayanan had a sudden heart attack and he passed away. At that time I was left completely broken - financially, emotionally and also totally lost in the pursuit of how to manage this wholly unknown social problem - the homeless person with severe mental illness. At that time the organization was new and had no resources to contemplate an institutional model also. At that point I had only two paths ahead of me. I could close the organization which was only 10 month old and pursue my professional career in corporate sector. Or I could plunge into the problem and find my way despite all the challenges. I decided to take the latter path. The rest is history.', '• Iswar Sankalpa has been working towards the protection of the rights of persons with psychosocial disabilities (primarily the homeless and slum-based population) since 2007– upholding their right to health services, right to comprehensive habilitation/rehabilitation, their right to employment, their right to safe housing and their right to access government facilities, entitlements and other benefits, by setting up a continuum of multi-pronged care and support. It has been striving to build a model of inclusive care for the most vulnerable and least legally protected population by designing and redesigning programmes and strategies based on their emerging needs. A combination of services (outreach, shelter, day care centre, clinic-based, community centred…) and reintegration support programmes (skills training, non-formal education, access to entitlements, community living, income generation programmes, selfadvocacy…) have been developed over the years since no one size fits all and no particular solution is the only solution to the complexities and the magnitude of the problem in hand. The work being rooted in the Community Based Rehabilitation (CBR) model is addressing 5 major aspects of living: Health, Education, Livelihood, Social and Empowerment. With the target group’s choice, agency and participation forming the nucleus of the work, the model underlines the importance of multi-sectoral collaboration (family of the primary stakeholders, law enforcement agency, government, medical body, community, civil society and media) for facilitating sustainable community reintegration of the vulnerable social groups. \r\n•	3440 homeless persons with psychosocial disability, living on the streets, have been provided treatment & services through community based care model\r\n•	604 women have been provided a safe shelter.\r\n•	129 men have been provided a safe shelter.\r\n•	468 persons have been restored to home across India\r\n•	775 persons with psychosocial disability are in employment\r\n•	716 persons have been provided vocational training\r\n•	120 persons have received ration card, 176 persons have received disability card, 264 persons have received adhar card and 171 persons have their own bank account.\r\n•	4633  persons from low income group families have been provided treatment, counseling & CBR support through Urban Mental Health Clinics\r\n•	895 awareness campaigns were conducted in the community for sensitization and education covering more than 51935 people\r\n•	288 health workers, medical officers and police personnel have been provided mental health training\r\n•	A network of 476 CBOs has been created to provide various support\r\n•	2 mental health committees have been formed involving local councillors, community leaders and community members', 'I would like to work to offer opportunities for our men/ women to be financially independent. I hope to have small kiosks/ shops in parts of the city where products made by persons with psychosocial disability are bought, used and recommended for their worth and not for sympathy. I want to see every person have a purpose in life.', 'https://www.telegraphindia.com/west-bengal/calcutta/who-recognition-for-city-ngo-which-helps-the-homeless/cid/1819321', '[{"download_link":"files/D77KwXClrshc114Dsj4RrKDBMGs9rshQT4Fxqzz0.jpg","original_name":"40 (2).JPG"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/G4k2mMR3Etfk5LXjqz1EnzvWoMPMU4D5DL6Wv60M.mp4","original_name":"Ashoka Video.mp4"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/0wPFJBb2cSX8wKn80sv0Q60fAv0Up4o4AG8bNQZQ.jpg","original_name":"State Award 3-12-19.jpeg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/KD09FfgrGJeg3NV5cQFHvwjUyhO6dGU4OpKDmpdD.jpg","original_name":"dr kalam and me.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/doUi6nqXzlYeEhnUfdr4tkpw9AmFfjIY1utEQu42.pdf","original_name":"Iswar Sankalpa_Annual report_2019-20.pdf"}]', '2021-11-16 20:57:40', '2021-11-16 20:57:40', NULL, 0),
	(64, 7, 'Y', 'Performing Arts (Music, Dance & Theatre)', 2, 'You Inspire (More than 10 years of experience)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Shashwati Garai Ghosh (inserted)', '1980-10-11', '9831734178', 'shashwatigg@gmail.com', '3 Charunagar, Brahmapur, Kolkata - 700096', 'https://www.youtube.com/user/shashwatigg', 'https://www.facebook.com/shashwati.garaighosh', 'https://www.instagram.com/shashwatigarai', 'https://www.facebook.com/Angashuddhi/', 'https://www.instagram.com/angashuddhi/', 'Hailing from a family of artists I grew to believe that art reflects life. As a child I was curious and creative, enjoyed movements and liked to be engaged in artistic activities. Learning dance at a very tender age gave me immense happiness then and later paved the way for a career in it.\r\n\r\nI always knew that I wanted to live with an art form. I also knew that I would do whatever it takes to train myself to become an independent artist with an individualistic approach to my chosen art form.  \r\n\r\nThat desire started taking shape when I joined my guru Sharmila Biswas years ago.\r\n\r\nI was intrigued by her approach towards Odishi and the vast body of work. I took things very slowly to understand every bit of the training, the research, the intricacies, and the volume of the process. \r\n\r\nMy dance career just flowed through these processes. And what I most enjoyed is the freedom within the hardcore professional life of an artiste.\r\n\r\nA very early start to my solo career gave me the necessary experience and confidence to start my own dance institute. My Institute ‘Angashuddhi – Home for Odishi’ is an initiative to nurture, and pass on the experience of learning Odishi dance to the next generation. I strive to encourage the appreciation of the Odishi dance form and imbibe its roots to dancers and art enthusiasts alike. \r\n\r\nI am very content as a dancer, and Odishi is my language of expression. I express my ideas, thoughts and creativity as a soloist, a choreographer, and a teacher.\r\n\r\nChallenges and hurdles exist. But they are part of an exciting journey.', 'Angashuddhi – Home for Odishi', 'Institute founder, soloist, choreographer, teacher', '22', '2021-06-30', '3 Charunagar, Brahmapur', 'Kolkata', 'West Bengal', '700096', '9831734178', 'shashwatigg@gmail.com', NULL, NULL, 'I have always been impressed, influenced, and intrigued by my guru Sharmila Biswas\' vast body of work. From her I learnt the importance of methodical research, and a deliberate approach to creating original work.\r\n\r\nI was privileged to receive special training from dance stalwarts like Guru Kelucharan Mohapatra, Smt. Kalanidhi Narayanan, Smt. Sonal Mansingh, Smt. Malavika Sarukkai, and Guru Durgacharan Ranbir. That association was priceless, and I gained critical strength and confidence helping me every step of my professional career.\r\n\r\nMy training with fitness expert Dr. Kannan Pugazhendi completely changed my perspective towards staying fit as a dancer. That learning helped me create my own dance fitness regime that I\'ve incorporated in my training method.\r\n\r\nAchievements:\r\n1. First recipient of Guru Kelucharan Mohapatra Yuva Pratibha Samman\r\n2. Ustad Bismillah Khan Yuva Puraskar\r\n3. Kalavahini Senior Fellowship\r\n4. Sanskriti Madhobi Chatterjee Memorial Fellowship\r\n5. National Scholarship, Ministry of Culture, Government of India.', 'Managing my solo career while also running my own dance institute, has been an ongoing challenge. I learn and overcome many hurdles everyday… It is a constant process.', 'As a performer and teacher of a classical dance form I believe I bear the responsibility of preserving and passing on a very rich cultural artefact. With my life\'s work I have strived to achieve that. In the process, I hope to leave my own footprints of artistic thoughts and ideas in the sand of time.', 'I would like to continue to create original work as a choreographer, and contribute further to my pedagogical repertoire.', NULL, '[{"download_link":"files/S1Ck5htowNnmJBlGMrHxfX7nBiOVwEXpdY6eAmjw.jpg","original_name":"Sgg.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/RtEiL7escOV8p5WhR7NFp6ZklejS7NJkKiTz2L49.mp4","original_name":"sgg video clip.mp4"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/5PCmcGFz2MDimq4SQaStrcG7RUME5Y3fqPHIN6C4.jpg","original_name":"Bismillah Khan Award.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/0xKQ6AGzQhCgXG1j3adqRke4TpczmCh1iXEp94n0.jpg","original_name":"Review.jpg"}]', '[{"download_link":"files/8ojpCMQIuoIMsEvo2yjsROYMF36trSFfxzTTq8gX.jpg","original_name":"Sgg.jpeg"}]', '2021-11-15 11:27:12', '2021-11-15 11:27:12', NULL, 0);
